== Timeline ==

=== 1 April ===
According to the information provided by the spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters in the morning, pro-Russian troops had opened fire on 11 occasions on Ukrainian positions on the last day of March<!--2 WIA--><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/01/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-31-bereznya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 31 березня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-01 |access-date=2018-04-01 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 10 occasions in [[Donetsk Oblast|Donetsk region]] and once in [[Luhansk Oblast|Luhansk region]]<ref name=_2018-04-01ru/>); the fire was returned once.<ref name=_2018-04-01ru/> The spokesman of the [[Ministry of Defence (Ukraine)|Ministry of Defence]] confirmed at noon that two Ukrainian servicemen were [[Wounded in action|wounded]] in the [[Donbass|Donbass region]] on 31 March.<ref name=_2018-04-01ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/65778-prauta-11 |title=Двое украинских военных получили ранения – полковник Праута |trans-title= |date=2018-01-01 |accessdate=2018-01-01 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> [[Donetsk People's Republic|Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city]] reported two Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in [[Staromykhailivka]] and [[Trudivske]], in the southern area of Donetsk city, using small arms and [[AGS-30|automatic grenade launchers]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-dvazhdy-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=ВСУ дважды нарушили режим прекращения огня — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-01|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-01|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local officials, the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire four times within the borders of the [[Luhansk People's Republic|self-styled Luhansk People's Republic]], when Ukrainian forces employed small arms, [[rocket launcher]]s, automatic grenade launchers, [[2B14 Podnos|82&nbsp;mm mortars]] and [[BMP-1]] armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mil-lnr.info/press-sluzhba/svodka/item/2396-operativnaya-svodka-za-sutki-s-31-marta-na-1-aprelya|title=Оперативная сводка за сутки с 31 марта на 1 апреля|last=|first=|date=1 April 2018|website=mil-lnr.info|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=1 April 2018}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on positions of [[Ukrainian Armed Forces|Ukrainian troops]] on 14 occasions, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1907123715965092 |title= Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 1 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=1 April 2018 |accessdate=1 April 2018 |publisher= |language=uk|website=www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts}}</ref> In the outskirts of Donetsk city, 82&nbsp;mm mortar volleys landed in [[Avdiivka]], Butivka mining complex and [[Pisky, Yasynuvata Raion|Pisky]]. Avdiivka and Butivka also became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. Rebel troops employed heavy machine guns to attack the villages of [[Kamianka, Yasynuvata Raion|Kamianka]], [[Verkhnyotoretske]] and [[Opytne, Yasynuvata Raion|Opytne]]. In the region of [[Mariupol]], [[Shyrokyne]] came under 82&nbsp;mm mortar fire. Ukrainian positions at [[Pavlopil]] and [[Vodiane, Volnovakha Raion|Vodiane]] were fired at with infantry weapons, sniper rifles and grenade launchers. Heavy machine guns targeted Ukrainian troops at [[Starohnativka]], [[Talakivka]] and [[Hnutove]]. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, Ukrainian redoubts at [[Luhanske, Bakhmut Raion|Luhanske]] were struck by small arms fire, heavy machine gun fire and 120&nbsp;mm mortar volleys. There was an 82&nbsp;mm mortar attack on Troitske, while small arms fire was reported at [[Stanytsia Luhanska]]. By the end of the day, rebel forces had committed 38 ceasefire violations.<ref name="MoD_1230-04-02_ru" /> Pro-Russian authorities told the press that the Ukrainian military opened fire at their positions at Vasiilivka and [[Zaitseve, Luhansk Oblast|Zaitseve]] using infantry weapons.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-vasilevke-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по Васильевке — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-01|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-01|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-zajtsevo-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Зайцево — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-01|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-01|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Later in the day, pro-Russian outposts at Spartak were struck by small arms fire, machine gun fire, automatically launched grenades and antitank rockets. Vasiilivka was attacked once again, this time with automatic grenade launchers. Separatist troops were harassed with small arms and heavy machine gun fire at Zabicheve.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/01/vsu-vedut-obstrel-naselennyh-punktov-dnr/|title=ВСУ ВЕДУТ ОБСТРЕЛ НАСЕЛЕННЫХ ПУНКТОВ ДНР|last=|first=|date=1 April 2018|website=News-Front|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=1 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-zhabichevo-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Жабичево — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-01|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-01|language=ru-RU}}</ref> [[BMP-2]] armoured vehicles from Avdiivka, supported by infantry weapons engaged pro-Russian redoubts at Oktyabrskiy Rudnik.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-posyolku-shahty-oktyabrskij-rudnik-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по поселку шахты "Октябрьский рудник" — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-01|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-01|language=ru-RU}}</ref> [[Yasynuvata]] was fired at by small arms, heavy machine guns and automatic grenade launchers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-yasinovataya-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Ясиноватая — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-01|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-01|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Sources from the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic said that Ukrainian forces hit and destroyed a military ambulance with an [[Anti-tank missile|antitank guided missile]] in the surroundings of [[Nyzhnie Lozove]]. The vehicle, a [[Ural Automotive Plant|URAL]] truck, was carrying a wounded soldier at the time of the incident. The driver, a paramedic and the wounded soldier were critically injured.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/01/kievskie-siloviki-unichtozhili-sanitarnyj-avtomobil-v-rajone-nizhnego-lozovogo-est-ranennye/|title=КИЕВСКИЕ СИЛОВИКИ УНИЧТОЖИЛИ САНИТАРНЫЙ АВТОМОБИЛЬ В РАЙОНЕ НИЖНЕГО ЛОЗОВОГО, ЕСТЬ РАНЕННЫЕ|last=|first=|date=1 April 2018|website=News-Front|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=1 April 2018}}</ref>

=== 2 April ===
The spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 38 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--no casualties--><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/02/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-1-kvitnya2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 1 квітня 2018 року |trans-title=Information by ATO HQ on 1 April 2018 |date=2 April 2018 |accessdate=2 April 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 32 occasions in Donetsk region and on 6 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=MoD_1230-04-02_ru/>). The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence reported at noon no casualties in the Donbass region on the first day of April.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-02_ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/65787-gutsulyak-42 |title=Боевики применили 120-мм и 82-мм минометы – полковник Гуцуляк |trans-title= |date=2018-03-31 |accessdate=2018-04-01 |publisher=MoD |language=ru}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported 16 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in six different locations using small arms, snipers, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-istekshie-sutki-vsu-16-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-predstavitelstvo-dnr-v-stskk/|title=За сутки ВСУ применили по территории Республики 149 единиц боеприпасов — Представительство ДНР в СЦКК / The total number of ammunition used by the AFU was 149 units — DPR Representative Office to the JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-02|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-02|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Sources from the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic recorded two Ukrainian violations of the truce within the republic's borders. The Ukrainian military used BMP-1 armoured vehicles and antitank guided missiles to engage pro-Russian troops at Nyzhnie Lozove. Three servicemen were injured.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-dva-raza-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-raneno-troe-voennosluzhashhih-nm-lnr/|title=ВСУ два раза нарушили режим прекращения огня, ранены трое военнослужащих — НМ ЛНР {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-02|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-02|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 10 occasions, exclusively in Donetsk region.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1908134385864025 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 2 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-02 |accessdate=2018-04-02 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day, there were 20 ceasefire violation along the demarcation line. In the otskirts of Donetsk city, 82&nbsp;mm mortar volleys landed in Pisky. Butivka mining complex became the target of small arms, snipers, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. Avdiivka and Kamianka were also hit by antitank rockets. In the region of Mariupol, Ukrainian troops at Vodiane were harassed with heavy machine gun fire, while Talakivka, Pavlopil, Hnutove, Vodiane and Shyrokyne came under small arms fire.<ref name=":4" /> Pro-Russian sources reported several Ukrainian violations of the truce by evening. The Ukrainian military carried out a number of attacks on Pikuzy using small arms, heavy machine guns and automatic grenade launchers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-kominternovo-iz-granatometa-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по Коминтерново из гранатомета — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-02|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-kominternovo-stskk/|title=ВСУ обстреляли Коминтерново — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-02|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref> The same kind of weapons were employed against Vasiliivka,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-vasilevka-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Васильевка — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-02|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref> while Spartak came under small arms and heavy machine gun fire.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-n-p-spartak-stskk/|title=Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по н.п. Спартак — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-02|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Uzhivka was hit by rocket propelled grenades.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-n-p-leninskoe-stskk/|title=Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по н.п. Ленинское — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-02|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref> BMP-1 armoured vehicles engaged pro-Russian positions at the outskirts of [[Horlivka]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-shahtu-v-rajone-gorlovki-stskk/|title=ВСУ обстреляли шахту в районе Горловки — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-02|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

=== 3 April ===
According to the information provided by the spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters in the morning, pro-Russian troops had opened fire on 20 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day,<!--no casualties--><ref name=":4">{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/03/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-2-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 2 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-03 |access-date=2018-04-03 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> exclusively in Donetsk region; the fire was returned once.<ref name=noon04-03ru/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence reported at noon no casualties in the Donbass region on 2 April.<ref name=noon04-03ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/65816-gutsulyak-43 |title=Боевики совершили 20 обстрелов – полковник Гуцуляк |trans-title= |date=2018-04-03 |accessdate=2018-04-03 |publisher=MoD |language=ru}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported 14 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in eight locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivali-territoriyu-respubliki-chetyrnadtsat-raz-stskk/|title=ВСУ обстреливали территорию Республики четырнадцать раз — СЦКК / APU shelled the Republic's territory fourteen times — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-03|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref> One pro-Russian soldier was killed in action.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/ukrainskie-boeviki-14-raz-narushili-peremirie-pogib-voennosluzhashhij-dnr-eduard-basurin/|title=Украинские боевики 14 раз нарушили перемирие, погиб военнослужащий ДНР – Эдуард Басурин (видео) / Ukrainian militants violated the truce 14 times, a DPR soldier was killed – Eduard Basurin (video) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-03|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 10 occasions, one Ukrainian soldier was wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1909237535753710 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 3 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=3 April 2018 |accessdate=3 April 2018 |publisher= |language=uk|website=www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts}}</ref> In the surroundings of Donetsk city, Opytne came under 82&nbsp;mm mortar fire, while Avdiivka and Pisky were hit by rocket propelled grenades. The separatists attacked Kamianka, Marinka and Butivka coal mine with infantry weapons, including sniper rifles. In the region of Mariupol, antitank rockets landed in Pishchevik and Vodiane. Small arms and sniper fire was reported at Vodiane and Shyrokyne. Pavlopil was the target of heavy machine guns. In the northern section of the demarcation line, the Ukrainian stronghold of Luhanske came under 82&nbsp;mm mortar fire, and Novooleksandrivka was hit by antitank rockets. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 24.<ref name=MoD6am04-04/> Pro-Russian authorities in Donetsk city told the press that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire several times at evening. In the outskirts of Donetsk city, Ukrainian BMP-1 armoured vehicles from Nevelske, supported by small arms and heavy machine guns engaged pro-Russian positions at Lozove.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-lozovomu-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по Лозовому — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-03|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Nearby Spartak became the target of infantry weapons, automatic grenade launchers and antitank rockets,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-spartak-iz-granatometa-stskk-2/|title=ВСУ обстреляли Спартак из гранатомета — СЦКК / AFU attacked Spartak with a grenade launcher — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-03|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-spartak-stskk-3/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Спартак — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-03|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref> while Kruta Balka and Yakovliivka were fired at from Avdiivka with small arms and heavy machine guns.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-krutaya-balka-stskk-2/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Крутая Балка — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-03|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-prigorodu-donetska-n-p-yakovlevka-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по пригороду Донецка (н.п. Яковлевка) — СЦКК / AFU opened fire on the suburb of Donetsk (p.l. Yakovlevka) — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-03|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Yasynuvata was meanwhile hit by small arms fire, machine gun fire and antitank rockets also fired from Avdiivka.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-ryadu-naselennyh-punktov-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по ряду населенных пунктов — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-03|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref> In the region of Mariupol, pro-Russian troops at Pikuzy and Uzhivka were harassed with small arms and sniper fire,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-kominternovo-stskk-2/|title=ВСУ обстреляли Коминтерново — СЦКК / AFU engaged Kominternovo — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-03|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-n-p-leninskoe-stskk-2/|title=Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по н.п. Ленинское — СЦКК / Shooting attack on Leninskoye was recorded from the side of the AFU — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-03|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref> while 120&nbsp;mm mortar rounds fired from Pavlopil landed around pro-Russian redoubts at Sosnovske.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-sosnovskoe-predstavitelstvo-dnr-v-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Сосновское — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-03|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Sniper fire from the direction of Vodiane was also reported at Dzerzhinske.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-dzerzhinskoe-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Дзержинское — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-03|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-03|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Ukrainian troops from Hnutove fired small arms and rocket launchers at the village of Novovyboivo.<ref name=":0" />

=== 4 April ===
The spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 24 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--1 WIA--><ref name=MoD6am04-04>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/04/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-3-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 3 квітня 2018 року |trans-title=Information by ATO HQ on 3 April 2018 |date=4 April 2018 |accessdate=4 April 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 22 occasions in Donetsk region and on 2 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=MoD_1230-04-04_ru/>); the fire was returned on 4 occasions.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-04_ru/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded in action in the Donbass region on 3 April.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-04_ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/65848-gutsulyak-44 |title=Боевики во время обстрелов применяют минометы, крупнокалиберные пулеметы и гранатометы – полковник Гуцуляк |trans-title= |date=2018-04-04 |accessdate=2018-04-04 |publisher=MoD |language=ru}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city recorded 16 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 12 locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, snipers, grenade launchers, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-istekshie-sutki-vsu-16-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=За истекшие сутки ВСУ 16 раз нарушили режим прекращения огня — СЦКК / AFU violated ceasefire 16 times during the past day — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-04|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-04|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local sources, the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire two times within the borders of the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian forces engaged pro-Russian positions at Nyzhne Lozove and Kalynivka employing small arms, automatic grenade launchers, rocket launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles and BMP-1 armoured vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-sutki-vsu-dva-raza-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-nm-lnr-2/|title=За сутки ВСУ два раза нарушили режим прекращения огня — НМ ЛНР {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-04|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-04|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 18 occasions, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1910827752261355 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 4 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-04 |accessdate=2018-04-04 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> Around Donetsk city, Butivka mining complex became the target of small arms, snipers, rocket launchers and 82&nbsp;mm mortars. Ukrainian positions at Avdiivka and Kamianka were struck by small arms fire, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. Antitank rockets also hit Marinka. the rebels used heavy machine guns to harass Ukrainian personnel at Opytne. In the region of Mariupol, armoured fighting vehicles, supported by infantry weapons, opened fire at Ukrainian redoubts near Hnutove, while small arms fire, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers targeted Lebedinske. Rocket propelled grenades were launched at Ukrainian positions at Vodiane, where small arms and sniper fire was also reported. Snipers were likewise active at Shyrokyne. Pavlopil and Lebedinske came under small arms fire. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, Ukrainian troops at Stanytsia Luhanska and Donets railway station received small arms fire. By the end of the day, the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 39.<ref name=FB6am_iv_05/> Pro-Russian authorities told the media that Ukrainian forces had attacked Pikuzy, Sakhanka, Uzhivka, Yasinuvata, Spartak, Zaitseve, Dzerzhinske and Trudivske. Among the main incidents, Spartak was shelled by 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles and 82&nbsp;mm mortars, while pro-Russian positions at Sakhanka were engaged by BMP-2 armoured vehicles. Zaitseve came under 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortar fire.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" /><ref name=":3" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-trudovskie-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Трудовские — СЦКК / AFU opened fire on Trudovskiye — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-04|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-05|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

=== 5 April ===
According to the information provided by the spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters in the morning, pro-Russian troops had opened fire on 39 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--no casualties--><ref name=FB6am_iv_05>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1911484485529015 |title= Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 4 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-05 |accessdate=2018-04-05 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 37 occasions in Donetsk and on 2 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=noon04-05ru/>). The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence reported at noon no casualties in the Donbass region on 4 April.<ref name=noon04-05ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/65872-gutsulyak-45 |title=Боевики совершили 39 прицельных обстрелов – полковник Гуцуляк |trans-title= |date=2018-04-05 |accessdate=2018-04-05 |publisher=MoD |language=ru}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city reported 15 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in eight different locations using small arms, snipers, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-2 armoured vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/ukrainskie-siloviki-prodolzhayut-obstrelivat-territoriyu-respubliki-daniil-bezsonov/|title=Украинские силовики продолжают обстреливать территорию Республики – Даниил Безсонов (видео) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-05|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-05|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-sahanka-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Саханка — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-04|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-05|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-spartak-stskk-4/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Спартак — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-04|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-05|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-yasinovataya-stskk-2/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Ясиноватая — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-04|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-05|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 10 occasions, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1911984608812336 |title= Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 5 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=5 April 2018 |accessdate=5 April 2018 |publisher= |language=uk|website=www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts}}</ref> In the area around Donetsk city, rebel troops fired small arms and rocket launchers at Ukrainian positions around Avdiivka, Novotroitske, Verkhnyotoretske and Butivka coal mine. Avdiivka and Nevelske also came under heavy machine gun fire. Small arms fire was reported at Kamianka, Berezove and Novomyhailivka. In the region of Mariupol, 120&nbsp;mm mortar volleys landed in Lebedinske. Marinka was fired at from small arms, sniper rifles, heavy machine guns, rocket launchers and 82&nbsp;mm mortars. Rebel forces fired small arms and several types of grenade launchers at Pavlopil. Small arms fire was reported at Talakivka. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, the separatists attacked Ukrainian positions at Luhanske with heavy machine guns, grenade launchers, 82&nbsp;mm mortars and 120&nbsp;mm mortars, Troitske was shelled with 82&nbsp;mm mortars, while Ukrainian troops at Novozvanivka came under small arms and heavy machine gun fire. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 27.<ref name=MoD6am04-06/> At Donetsk city, pro-Russian authorities said that the Ukrainian military had broken the ceasefire in several locations along the demarcation line, including Vasiliivka, Spartak, Olenivka, Lozove, [[Staromykhailivka]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-staromihajlovka-stskk/|title= ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Старомихайловка — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-05|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-05|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Verkhnyotoretske and Petrovsky district in the outskirts of Donetsk city,<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-donetsku-petrovskij-rajon-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Донецку (Петровский район) — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР]<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-spartak-stskk-5/ ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Спартак — СЦКК]<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-olenovka-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Оленовка — СЦКК / AFU opened fire on Olenovka — JCCC]<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-vasilevke-stskk-2/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Васильевке — СЦКК]<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-verhnetoretskoe-nizhnee-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Верхнеторецкое Нижнее — СЦКК ]</ref> and in the region of Mariupol, Sakhanka, Dzerzhinske and Uzhivka. The main actions took place at Uzhivka, where BMP-1 armoured vehicles engaged pro-Russian redoubts supported by 120&nbsp;mm mortar fire<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vnov-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-leninskoe-stskk/|title=ВСУ вновь открыли огонь по н.п. Ленинское — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-05|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-05|language=ru-RU}}</ref> nearby Sakhanka, also hit by 120&nbsp;mm mortar rounds,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-sahanka-stskk-3/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Саханка — СЦКК (обновлено) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-05|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-05|language=ru-RU}}</ref> and Dzerzhinske, which became the target of automatic grenade launchers and 73&nbsp;mm antitank rockets.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-dzerzhinskomu-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по Дзержинскому — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-05|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-05|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Lozove was shelled by BMP-2 armoured vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-lozovoe-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Лозовое — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-05|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-05|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

=== 6 April ===
The spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 27 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--no casualties--><ref name=MoD6am04-06>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/06/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-5-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 5 квітня 2018 року |trans-title=Information by ATO HQ on 1 April 2018 |date=6 April 2018 |accessdate=6 April 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 23 occasions in Donetsk and on 4 occasion in Luhansk region<ref name=MoD_1230-04-06_uk/>); the fire was returned on 3 occasions.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-06_uk/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence reported at noon no casualties in the Donbass region on 5 April.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-06_uk>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/06/brifing-rechnika-ministerstva-oboroni-ukraini-shhodo-situaczii-na-linii-zitknennya/ |title=Брифінг речника Міністерства оборони України щодо ситуації на лінії зіткнення |trans-title= |date=2018-04-06 |accessdate=2018-04-06 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported 16 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 11 different locations using small arms, snipers, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-za-sutki-devyatnadtsat-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=ВСУ за сутки девятнадцать раз нарушили режим прекращения огня — СЦКК / AFU violated the ceasefire nineteen times during the day — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-06|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-06|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Deputy minister of defence from the self-styled Donetsk People's Republic, [[Eduard Basurin]], recorded in his daily briefing 101 Ukrainian violations of the truce over the past week, with 120 rounds fired from 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortars, weapons banned by the Minsk agreements. Two pro-Russian soldiers were killed by snipers on the same period.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/06/razvedka-dnr-vyyavila-u-fronta-svyshe-60-edinits-tyazhelogo-vooruzheniya-vsu-vklyuchaya-rszo-artorudiya-i-tanki/|title=РАЗВЕДКА ДНР ВЫЯВИЛА У ФРОНТА СВЫШЕ 60 ЕДИНИЦ ТЯЖЕЛОГО ВООРУЖЕНИЯ ВСУ, ВКЛЮЧАЯ РСЗО, АРТОРУДИЯ И ТАНКИ|last=|first=|date=6 April 2018|website=News-Front|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=15 April 2018}}</ref> Local authorities from the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic denounced two Ukrainian violations of the truce inside the republic boundaries. The Ukrainian army pounded pro-Russian positions at Kalynivka and Dolhe with small arms, automatic grenade launchers, rocket launchers and 82&nbsp;mm mortars.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-sutki-vsu-dva-raza-obstrelyali-territoriyu-luganshhiny-primeniv-granatomety-i-minomety-nm-lnr/|title=За сутки ВСУ два раза обстреляли территорию Луганщины, применив гранатометы и минометы — НМ ЛНР / AFU twice attacked the territory of the Lugansk region with grenade launchers and mortars — LPR PM {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-06|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-07|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 16 occasions, two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1913149898695807 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 6 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-06 |accessdate=2018-04-06 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> In the surroundings of Donetsk city, Pisky was shelled with 82&nbsp;mm mortars, while Avdiivka and Marinka came under small arms and rocket propelled grenade fire. Rebel troops fired small arms at Krasnohorivka, Butivka coal mine, Kamianka and Pisky. In the region of Mariupol, pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian redoubts at Shyrokyne supported by 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery. Lebedinske was hit by heavy machine gun fire and antitank rockets, while Ukrainian troops became the target of infantry weapons at Talakivka, Hnutove and Pavlopil. Sniper activity was reported at Shyrokyne. In the northern section of the demarcation line, Luhanske and Novoluhanske were fired at from small arms, heavy machine guns, rocket launchers, 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortars. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles opened fire at Ukrainian redoubts near Troitske, which were also targeted by heavy machine guns and 82&nbsp;mm mortars. valuiske was shelled with 120&nbsp;mm mortars. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 42.<ref name=MoD6am04-07/> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city told the press that the Ukrainian military attacked Spartak, Yasynuvata, Mineralne, Vasiilivka, Dokuchaievsk and Petrovsky district, in the outskirts of Donetsk city, Shyroka Balka and Dolomitne in the area of Horlivka, and in the region of Mariupol, Sakhanka and Uzhivka. Ukrainian forces used small arms, snipers, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles. In the main incidents, Shyroka Balka was shelled with 120&nbsp;mm mortars, while 82&nbsp;mm mortar volleys landed in Sakhanka, Leninske, Dolomitne and Yasynuvata. BMP-1 armoured fighting vehicles opened fire on pro-Russian entrenchments at Sakhanka, Yasynuvata, Dokuchaievsk and Dolomitne. One pro-Russian soldier was killed by snipers at Mineralne.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-minometnyj-ogon-po-sahanke-stskk-2/ ВСУ открыли минометный огонь по Саханке — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vnov-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-leninskoe-stskk-2/ ВСУ вновь открыли огонь по н.п. Ленинское — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-minometnyj-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-n-p-dolomitnoe-stskk/ Зафиксирован минометный обстрел со стороны ВСУ по н.п. Доломитное — СЦКК (обновлено) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-yasinovatoj-stskk-2/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Ясиноватой — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-dokuchaevsku-stskk-2/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Докучаевску — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/segodnya-utrom-snajperskim-ognem-ubit-voennosluzhashhij-dnr-stskk/ Сегодня утром снайперским огнем убит военнослужащий ДНР — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/su-otkryli-ogon-po-spartaku-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Спартаку — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-shirokaya-balka-stskk-2/ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Широкая Балка — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-sahanku-iz-bmp-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Саханку из БМП — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].</ref>

=== 7 April ===
According to the information provided by the spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters in the morning, pro-Russian troops had opened fire on 42 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--2 WIA--><ref name=MoD6am04-07>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/07/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-6-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 6 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-07 |access-date=2018-04-07 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 32 occasions in Donetsk region and on 10 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=noon04-07ru/>); the fire was returned on 18 occasions.<ref name=noon04-07ru/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 6 April.<ref name=noon04-07ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/65961-hutsulyak-21 |title=Боевики 42 раза открыли огонь в сторону сил АТО, два украинских военных ранены – полковник Гуцуляк |trans-title= |date=2018-04-07 |accessdate=2018-04-07 |publisher=MoD |language=ru |location= [[Kiev]] }}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city recorded 23 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in ten different areas using small arms, heavy machine guns, snipers, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles. The same sources reported the death of one pro-Russian serviceman.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-sutki-vsu-primenili-po-territorii-respubliki-305-boepripasov-stskk/|title=За сутки ВСУ применили по территории Республики 305 боеприпасов — СЦКК / AFU fired 305 rounds on the territory of the Republic during the day — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-07|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-07|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local officials, the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire four times within the borders of the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic, when Ukrainian forces employed small arms, automatic grenade launchers, rocket launchers, 82&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured fighting vehicles attacked pro-Russian forces at Kalynivka and Kalynove.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/07/lnr-operativnaya-svodka-obstrelyany-dva-poselka/|title=ЛНР: ОПЕРАТИВНАЯ СВОДКА — ОБСТРЕЛЯНЫ ДВА ПОСЕЛКА|last=|first=|date=7 April 2018|website=News-Front|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=7 April 2018}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 17 occasions, one Ukrainian soldier was wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1914200181924112 |title= Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 7 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=7 April 2018 |accessdate=7 April 2018 |publisher= |language=uk|website=www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts}}</ref> In the area of Donetsk city, rebel forces opened fire at Ukrainian positions with small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. Small arms fire and antitank rockets struck Avdiivka and Butivka mining complex, while Ukrainian troops at Krasnohorivka were harassed with small arms fire. Sniper fire was reported at Slavne. In the region of Mariupol, antitank guided missiles were fired at Pishchevik, while Talakivka and Vodiane became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. Rebel snipers opened fire on Ukrainian personnel at Talakivka, Pavlopil and Shyrokyne. Ukrainian forces at Pavlopil, Shyrokyne, Hnutove and Pishchevik received small arms fire. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, Ukrainian positions at Luhanske were engaged with heavy machine guns, rocket launchers and 82&nbsp;mm mortars. Nearby Malynove became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 42.<ref name=MoD6am04-08/> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city told the press that Ukrainian forces attacked Spartak, Yasynuvata, Kruta Balka, Olenivka and Dokuchaievsk, in the outskirts of Donetsk city, Dolomitne in the area of Horlivka, and in the region of Mariupol, Sakhanka, Yelenivka and Uzhivka. The Ukrainian military used small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-2 armoured vehicles. The incidents involved the shelling of Dolomitne from 120&nbsp;mm mortars and Sakhanka and Lozove from 82&nbsp;mm mortars. Ukrainian BMP-2 armoured vehicles engaged pro-Russian troops at Spartak.<ref>[https://dnr-online.ru/v-rezultate-obstrela-so-storony-vsu-na-kpvv-olenovka-ranena-zhenshhina-stskk/ В результате обстрела со стороны ВСУ на КПВВ «Оленовка» ранена женщина — СЦКК / A woman was wounded by the AFU's shooting at the Olenovka checkpoint — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-krutoj-balke-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Крутой Балке — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-elenovke-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Еленовке — СЦКК / AFU opened fire on Yelenovka — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-yasinovatoj-stskk-5/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Ясиноватой — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-v-ocherednoj-raz-otkryli-ogon-po-sahanke-stskk-2/ ВСУ в очередной раз открыли огонь по Саханке — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-lozovomu-stskk-2/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Лозовому — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-dolomitnomu-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Доломитному — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vnov-otkryli-ogon-po-spartak-stskk/ ВСУ вновь открыли огонь по Спартаку — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-naselennyj-punkt-leninskoe-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли населенный пункт Ленинское — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР], 2018-04-08.</ref>

=== 8 April ===
The spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 42 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--1 WIA--><ref name=MoD6am04-08>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/08/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-7-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 5 квітня 2018 року |trans-title=Information by ATO HQ on 1 April 2018 |date=8 April 2018 |accessdate=8 April 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 38 occasions in Donetsk region and on 4 occasion in Luhansk region<ref name=MoD_1230-04-08_uk/>); 4 ceasefire violations were registered during the first half of 8 April.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-08_uk/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded in action in the Donbass region on 7 April.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-08_uk>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/08/brifing-rechnika-ministerstva-oboroni-ukraini-shhodo-situaczii-na-linii-zitknennya/ |title=Брифінг речника Міністерства оборони України щодо ситуації на лінії зіткнення |trans-title= |date=2018-04-08 |accessdate=2018-04-08 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city reported 19 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in eight locations using small arms, snipers, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles. Two pro-Russian soldiers were killed by Ukrainian snipers, one female civilian was wounded.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-devyatnadtsat-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=ВСУ девятнадцать раз нарушили режим прекращения огня – СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-08|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-08|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Sources from the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic recorded three Ukrainian violations of the truce within the republic's borders. The Ukrainian military used 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles and 120&nbsp;mm mortars to engage pro-Russian troops at Veselehorivka and Kalynove. One serviceman was killed and another wounded by mortar fire at Veselehorivka.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/08/lnr-operativnaya-svodka-obstrelyany-dva-poselka-est-pogibshie-i-ranenye/|title=ЛНР: ОПЕРАТИВНАЯ СВОДКА — ОБСТРЕЛЯНЫ ДВА ПОСЕЛКА, ЕСТЬ ПОГИБШИЕ И РАНЕНЫЕ|last=|first=|date=8 April 2018|website=News-Front|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=8 April 2018}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening of [[Russian Orthodox Church|Orthodox]] [[Easter|Easter Sunday]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/pozdravlenie-glavy-dnr-po-sluchayu-voskreseniya-hristova/|title=Поздравление Главы ДНР по случаю Воскресения Христова {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-08|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-09|language=ru-RU}}</ref> as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 12 occasions, four Ukrainian servicemen were wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/08/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-stanom-na-18-00-8-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 8 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-08 |accessdate=2018-04-08 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> Around Donetsk city, Kaminaka became the target of small arms and rocket launchers, while Ukrainian troops at Avdiivka and Butivka mining complex came under small arms fire. In the region of Mariupol, pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian positions at Bohdanivka, supported by small arms fire. Heavy machine gun fire harassed Ukrainian forces at Vodiane, Hnutove and Pishchevyk, while Lebedinske, Vodiane, Pishevyk and Shyrokyne were raked by small arms fire. Hostile snipers were active at Shyrokyne. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, rebel forces opened fire on Ukrainian positions with heavy machine guns, rocket launchers, 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortars. Ukrainian troops at Svitlodarsk, meanwhile, became the target of snipers, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers. Antitank rockets struck nearby Krymske and Valuiske. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 35 and one more Ukrainian soldier was wounded.<ref name=MoD6am04-09/> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city told the press that Ukrainian forces opened fire on their troops at Spartak, Kruta Balka and Vasiilivka, in the area of Donetsk city, and Uzhivka and Pikuzy, in the region of Mariupol. The Ukrainian military employed small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, rocket launchers, 82&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles. In the main incidents, Uzhivka came under 82&nbsp;mm mortars and pro-Russian redoubts at Pikuzy were engaged by BMP-1 armoured vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-prodolzhayut-vesti-ogon-po-n-p-vasilevka-stskk-2/|title=ВСУ продолжают вести огонь по н.п. Васильевка — СЦКК (обновлено) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-08|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-09|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-minomyotnyj-ogon-po-n-p-leninskoe-stskk/|title=ВСУ открыли миномётный огонь по н.п. Ленинское — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-08|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-09|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-kominternovo-stskk-3/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Коминтерново — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-08|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-09|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/u-povtorno-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-krutaya-balka-stskk/|title=ВСУ повторно открыли огонь по н.п. Крутая Балка — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-08|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-09|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-spartak-stskk-7/|title=ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Спартак — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-08|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-09|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

=== 9 April ===
According to the information provided by the spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters in the morning, pro-Russian troops had opened fire on 35 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--5 WIA--><ref name=MoD6am04-09>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/09/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-8-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 8 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-09 |access-date=2018-04-09 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 27 occasions in Donetsk and on 9 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=noon04-09ru/>). The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that five Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in the Donbass region on 8 April.<ref name=noon04-09ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/65973-gutsulyak-47 |title=Боевики совершили 36 прицельных обстрелов украинских позиций – полковник Гуцуляк |trans-title= |date=2018-04-09 |accessdate=2018-04-09 |publisher=MoD |language=ru |location= [[Kiev]] }}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city recorded 19 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in eight different areas using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, rocket launchers, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/ukrainskie-siloviki-prodolzhayut-obstrelivat-territoriyu-respubliki-eduard-basurin/|title=Украинские силовики продолжают обстреливать территорию Республики – Эдуард Басурин {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-09|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-09|language=ru-RU}}</ref> The same sources denounced a Ukrainian attempt to slip through the demarcation line in the area of Zaitseve, north of Horlivka. The incursion was repelled by the separatists, who claimed that two Ukrainian servicemen were killed. Two pro-Russian soldiers died in the engagement.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/ukrainskaya-drg-sovershila-napadenie-na-pozitsii-vs-dnr-ataka-byla-otbita-eduard-basurin/|title=Украинская ДРГ совершила нападение на позиции ВС ДНР, атака была отбита – Эдуард Басурин {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-09|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-09|language=ru-RU}}</ref> After an extensive search, which resulted in the death of another pro-Russian serviceman by small arms fire on 12 April, the corpse of the Ukrainian soldier was recovered by rebel forces and handed back to Ukrainian authorities on 15 April at Marinka.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/predstavitelstvo-dnr-v-stskk-sodejstvovalo-peredache-tela-diversanta-vsu-ukrainskoj-storone/|title=Представительство ДНР в СЦКК содействовало передаче тела диверсанта ВСУ украинской стороне {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-15|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-15|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local sources, the Ukrainian army broke the ceasefire on two occasions within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. Ukrainian BMP-1 armoured vehicles from Luhanske attacked pro-Russian positions at Lozove and Kalynivka supported by automatic grenade launchers, ZU-23-2 antiaircraft guns and 82&nbsp;mm mortars.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/09/lnr-operativnaya-svodka-dva-narusheniya-peremiriya-za-sutki/|title=ЛНР: ОПЕРАТИВНАЯ СВОДКА — ДВА НАРУШЕНИЯ ПЕРЕМИРИЯ ЗА СУТКИ|last=|first=|date=9 April 2018|website=News-Front|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=9 April 2018}}</ref>

The press-centre of the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 18 occasions, three Ukrainian soldiers were wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1916453461698784 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 9 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=9 April 2018 |accessdate=9 April 2018 |publisher= |language=uk|website=www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts}}</ref> In the outskirts of Donetsk city, antitank rockets hit Ukrainian positions at Kamianka, Marinka, Opytne and Avdiivka. From Marinka also came reports of heavy machine gun fire. Ukrainian troops at Pisky were harassed by hostile snipers and by small arms fire at Butivka coal mine and Pervomaisk. In the region of Mariupol, 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled guns opened fire on Ukrainian redoubts at Lebedinske and Shyrokyne, while 120&nbsp;mm mortar rounds landed in Vodiane. Lebedinske was later fired at from small arms and 82&nbsp;mm mortars. Rebel forces fired rocket launchers at Shyrokyne, Talakivka and Vodiane, while Pishchevyk was hit by heavy machine gun fire. Small arms fire was reported at Hnutove, Lebedinske, and Pavlopil. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, the separatists fired heavy machine guns and grenade launchers at Luhanske. Rocket propelled grenades also hit Ukrainian positions around Svitlodarsk and Katerinivka. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 35.<ref name=MoD6am04-10/> At Donetsk city, pro-Russian authorities said that the Ukrainian military had broken the ceasefire in several locations along the demarcation line, including Vasiliivka, Mineralne, Kulikove, Staromyhailivka, Abakumove coal mine, Spartak and Petrovsky district in the outskirts of Donetsk city, and in the region of Mariupol Sakhanka, Pikuzy, Petrovske, Uzhivka and Dzerzhinske. Ukrainian forces opened fire on pro-Russian positions using small arms, sniper rifles, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers. 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, antitank guided missiles and 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery. In the main incidents, 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled guns firing from Vodiane engaged pro-Russian forces at Uzhivka, while 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortar volleys fired from Shyrokyne landed in Sakhanka. Ukrainian troops from Talakivka launched antitank guided missiles at Pikuzy. Mineralne came under 120&nbsp;mm mortar fire.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivayut-poselok-spartak-stskk/ ВСУ обстреливают поселок Спартак – СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/nochyu-vsu-obstrelivali-kulikovo-i-mineralnoe-stskk/ Ночью ВСУ обстреливали Куликово и Минеральное — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-shahte-abakumova-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по шахте Абакумова — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-prodolzhayut-vesti-ogon-po-n-p-petrovskoe-stskk/ ВСУ продолжают вести огонь по н.п. Петровское — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР]• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-iz-tyayazhelogo-vooruzheniya-po-n-p-leninskoe-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь из тяяжелого вооружения по н.п. Ленинское — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-mineralnomu-i-leninskomu-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Минеральному и Ленинскому — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-staromihajlovka-stskk-2/ ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Старомихайловка — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vasilevka-pod-obstrelom-vsu-stskk/ Васильевка под обстрелом ВСУ — СЦКК (обновляется) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-kominternovo-stskk-4/ ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Коминтерново — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-prodolzh