=== 12 April ===
The spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 38 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--no casualties--><ref name=MoD6am04-12>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/12/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-11-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 11 квітня 2018 року |trans-title=Information by ATO HQ on 9 April 2018 |date=12 April 2018 |accessdate=12 April 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 36 occasions in Donetsk region and on 2 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=noon04-12ru/>). The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence reported at noon no casualties in the Donbass region on 11 April.<ref name=noon04-12ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/66033-gutsulyak-50 |title=Боевики обстреляли жилые кварталы Авдеевки – полковник Гуцуляк |trans-title= |date=2018-04-12 |accessdate=2018-04-12 |publisher=MoD |language=ru |location=}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city recorded 27 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 13 locations using small arms, snipers, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, antiaircraft guns, armoured personnel carriers, armoured fighting vehicles and 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-sutki-vsu-primenili-po-territorii-respubliki-587-boepripasov-stskk/|title=За сутки ВСУ применили по территории Республики 587 боеприпасов — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-12|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-12|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local sources, the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire two times within the borders of the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian forces engaged pro-Russian positions at Kalynove-Borshchevate and Kalynivka employing automatic grenade launchers, 82&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/12/lnr-operativnaya-svodka-obstrelyany-dva-poselka-2/|title=ЛНР: ОПЕРАТИВНАЯ СВОДКА – ОБСТРЕЛЯНЫ ДВА ПОСЕЛКА|last=|first=|date=12 April 2018|website=News-Front|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=12 April 2018}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 28 occasions, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1919804008030396 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 12 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-12 |accessdate=2018-04-12 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 66, one Ukrainian soldier was killed and another wounded. In the outskirts of Donetsk city, 120&nbsp;mm mortar volleys struck Pisky, while Butivka mining complex came under 82&nbsp;mm mortar fire. Ukrainian positions at Butivka and Opytne were also engaged by ZU-23-2 antiaircraft guns and armoured fighting vehicles. Marinka, Avdiivka, Opytne and Krasnohorivka became the target of infantry weapons and rocket launchers. Hostile snipersopened fire at Avdiivka and Pisky. In the region of Mariupol, Talakivka was hit by 82&nbsp;mm mortar fire, while pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles, supported by Zu-23-2 antiaircraft guns, opened fire on Ukrainian forces at Vodiane and Talakivka. The separatists fired small arms, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers at Lebedinske, Hnutove and Shyrokyne. Sniper fire was reported at Pavlopil. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, Troitske was shelled from 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, ZU-23-2 antiaircraft guns and armoured fighting vehicles. Nearby Krymske was hit by 82&nbsp;mm mortar fire. Ukrainian redoubts at Luhanske were shelled by ZU-23-2 antiaircraft guns and armoured fighting vehicles. Zaitseve, Novozvanivka, Artemove and Svitlodarsk were fired at from infantry weapons and antitank rocket launchers.<ref name=MoD6am04-13/> Intense hostile fire was reported by pro-Russian authorities along the demarcation line throughout the day. In the main incidents, Ukrainian BMP-1 and BMP-2 from Bohdanivka opened fire at pro-Russian positions around Petrovske, in the region of Mariupol, on several occasions. BMP-1 vehicles from Talakivka also shelled nearby Pikuzy, while Novolaspa became the target of BMP-2's cannon fire. In the area of Horlivka, one pro-Russian soldier was killed when Zaitseve came under heavy small arms fire. Holmivsky was fired at from antiaircraft artillery. Ukrainian armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles from Troitske engaged pro-Russian redoubts at Ozeryanivka, which was also hit by 82&nbsp;mm mortar rounds. BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Novhorodske opened fire on pro-Russian forces at Shyroka Balka. In the outskirts of Donetsk city, Spartak was shelled several times with 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortars. Volvo-Center and Vesele were hit by 82&nbsp;mm mortar rounds. Antiaircraft artillery fire was also reported at Vesele, and BMP-2 armoured vehicles opened fire at Bela Kamianka.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vedut-massirovannyj-obstrel-naselennyh-punktov-dnr-stskk/ ВСУ ведут массированный обстрел населенных пунктов ДНР — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vedut-ogon-po-neskolkim-napravleniyam-stskk/ ВСУ ведут огонь по нескольким направлениям — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vedut-ogon-po-chetyrem-napravleniyam-stskk/|title=ВСУ ведут огонь по четырем направлениям — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/pod-ognem-vsu-kominternovo-i-veseloe-stskk/ Под огнем ВСУ Коминтерново и Веселое — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-shirokoj-balke-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Широкой Балке — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-ubili-soldata-vs-dnr-kotoryj-spasal-detej-ot-obstrela-mo-dnr/ ВСУ убили солдата ВС ДНР, который спасал детей от обстрела — МО ДНР {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР], 2018-04-13</ref>

=== 13 April ===
According to the information provided by the spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters in the morning, pro-Russian troops had opened fire on 66 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--1 KIA, 1 WIA--><ref name=MoD6am04-13>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/13/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-12-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 12 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-13 |access-date=2018-04-13 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 54 occasions in Donetsk and on 12 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=noon04-13ru/>); the fire was returned on 20 occasions.<ref name=noon04-13ru/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian serviceman was killed and another wounded in the Donbass region on 12 April.<ref name=noon04-13ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/66061-gutsulyak-51 |title=В зоне АТО один украинский военный погиб – полковник Гуцуляк|trans-title= |date=2018-04-13 |accessdate=2018-04-13 |publisher=MoD |language=ru|quote=Один украинский военный погиб, еще один – получил ранения. Состояние его здоровья – тяжелое.}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city reported 45 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 23 areas using small arms, sniper rifles, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, antiaircraft guns, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vypustili-po-territorii-respubliki-svyshe-tysyachi-boepripasov-stskk/|title=ВСУ выпустили по территории Республики свыше тысячи боеприпасов — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-13|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-14|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to the same sources, there were 182 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire over the past week. Three pro-Russian soldiers were killed in action and seven civilian residents wounded. The Ukrainian army opened fire 55 times with 152&nbsp;mm and 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery and 705 times with 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortars.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-nedelyu-iz-za-obstrelov-so-storony-vsu-pogiblo-tri-voennosluzhashhih-dnr-raneno-sem-mirnyh-grazhdan-eduard-basurin/|title=За неделю из-за обстрелов со стороны ВСУ погибли трое военнослужащих ДНР, ранены семеро мирных граждан – Эдуард Басурин (видео) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-13|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-15|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Local officials reported that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire on five occasions within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian army employed 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured fighting vehicles to attack pro-Russian positions at Kalynove, Kalynove-Borshchevate, Sentianivka, Sanzharivka and Pervomaisk.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://riafan.ru/1046583-ukrainskie-siloviki-vypustili-po-lnr-110-snaryadov-za-sutki|title=Украинские силовики выпустили по ЛНР 110 снарядов за сутки|last=Иванова|first=Анна|work=Федеральное агентство новостей No.1|access-date=2018-04-14}}</ref>

The press-centre of the JFO reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 20 occasions, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1920965317914265 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 11 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=13 April 2018 |accessdate=13 April 2018 |publisher= |language=uk|website=www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts}}</ref> Around Donetsk city, 82&nbsp;mm mortar volleys struck Opytne and Kamianka, while antitank rockets landed in Avdiivka, Kamianka and Marinka. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles opened fire on Ukrainian redoubts at Kamianka, and heavy machine gun fire raked Ukrainian positions at Nevelske, Avdiivka, Marinka and Butivka mining complex. Small arms fire was reported at Opytne, Kamianka and Butivka. Rebel snipers harassed Ukrainian troops at Avdiivka. In the region of Mariupol, rebel forces fired rocket propelled grenades at Vodiane, Pavlopil, Bohdanivka and Lebedinske and heavy machine guns at Pavlopil. Ukrainian positions at Talakivka and Bohdanivka were shelled by armoured fighting vehicles. Small arms fire was reported at Lebedinske, Pavlopil, Talakivka and Vodiane. In the northern section of the demarcation line, armoured fighting vehicles opened fire on Ukrainian redoubts at Troitske supported by heavy machine guns, rocket launchers, 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortars. Krymske was hit by 82&nbsp;mm mortar fire, and Zaitseve by small arms fire and antitank rockets. The separatists fired heavy machine guns at Svitlodarsk. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 43, one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded.<ref name=MoD6am04-14/> Pro-Russian authorities told the press that Ukrainian forces attacked Mineralne, Trudivske, Spartak, Kruta Balka, Dokuchaievsk, in the outskirts of Donetsk city, Uzhivka, Sosnovske and Petrovske, in the region of Mariupol, and, in the area of Horlivka, Gagarin mining complex, Dolomitne and Ozeryanivka. In the main incidents, Spartak was repeatedly hit by 82&nbsp;mm mortar fire, while BMP-1 armoured vehicles engaged pro-Russian positions at Ozeryanivka, Kruta Balka, Sosnovske and Gagarin mining complex. BMP-2 armoured vehicles opened fire at Trudivske, Petrovske and Spartak, while antiaircraft fire raked Gagarin mining complex.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-chetyrem-napravleniyam-stskk/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по четырем направлениям — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-krutoj-balke-i-spartaku-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Крутой Балке и Спартаку — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-n-p-leninskoe-stskk-4/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по н.п. Ленинское — СЦКК ].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-dokuchaevska-stskk/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ Докучаевска — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-n-p-sosnovskoe-stskk/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по н.п. Сосновское — СЦКК ].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-petrovskoe-stskk-5/ ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Петровское — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-prodolzhayut-obstrel-n-p-spartak-stskk/ ВСУ продолжают обстрел н.п. Спартак — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-krutaya-balka-i-n-p-spartak-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Крутая Балка и н.п. Спартак — СЦКК ].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-ozeryanovka-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Озеряновка — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-spartak-stskk-11/ ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Спартак — СЦКК ].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-leninskoe-stskk-5/ ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Ленинское — СЦКК].</ref>

=== 14 April ===
The spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 43 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--1 WIA--><ref name=MoD6am04-14>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/14/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-13-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 13 квітня 2018 року |trans-title=Information by ATO HQ on 13 April 2018 |date=14 April 2018 |accessdate=14 April 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 39 occasions in Donetsk and on 4 occasions in Luhansk region). The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded in action in the Donbass region on 13 April.<ref name=noon04-14ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/66074-gutsulyak-52 |title=Боевики совершили 43 обстрела, применили минометы – полковник Гуцуляк |trans-title= |date=2018-04-14 |accessdate=2018-04-14 |publisher=MoD |language=ru}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city recorded 19 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 12 different areas using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, antiaircraft guns, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-sutki-vsu-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-19-raz-stskk/|title=За сутки ВСУ нарушили режим прекращения огня 19 раз — СЦКК / AFU violated the ceasefire 19 times during the day — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-14|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-14|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local officials, the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire four times within the borders of the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic. Ukrainian forces employed small arms, heavy machine guns, 82&nbsp;mm mortars and 120&nbsp;mm mortars to pound pro-Russian redoubts at Zholobok, Lozove, Sentianivka and Obozne.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://goves.net/news/1360-operativnaja-svodka-za-sutki-s-13-aprelja-na-14-aprelja.html|title=Оперативная сводка за сутки с 13 апреля на 14 апреля|website=Социальная сеть Новороссии|access-date=2018-04-14}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 28 occasions, one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1922108834466580 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 14 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-14 |accessdate=2018-04-14 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> In the surroundings of Donetsk city, rebel forces shelled Pisky and Butivka coal mine with 82&nbsp;mm mortars. Antitank rockets struck Ukrainian outposts at Avdiivka, Kamianka, Butivka coal mine and Marinka. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian positions at Novotroitske. Ukrainian troops at Avdiivka came under small arms and antiaircraft direct fire. Heavy machine gun fire was reported at Novotroitske and Butivka coal mine, while Ukrainian troops were harassed by small arms fire at Kamianka and Novomykhailivka and by sniper fire at Butivka. In the region of Mariupol, 122&nbsp;mm artillery barrages landed in Shyrokyne, while different types of grenade launchers were fire at Vodiane, Lebedinske and Talakivka. Ukrainian redoubts at Vodiane were fired at by armoured fighting vehicles. Ukrainian forces at Pavlopil, Hnutove, Lebedinske and Vodiane were targeted by heavy machine guns, and by small arms at Shyrokyne, Pavlopil, Lebedinske and Talakivka. Snipers opened fire on Ukrainian personnel at Talakivka. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, Zaitseve was struck by 120&nbsp;mm mortar fire. Pro-Russian rebels attacked nearby Luhanske with heavy machine guns, rocket launchers, 82&nbsp;mm mortars and armoured fighting vehicles. Ukrainian redoubts at Mayorsk became the target of heavy machine guns and rocket launchers, while heavy machine gun fire struck Troitske. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 52, two more Ukrainian soldiers were wounded.<ref name=MoD6am04-15/> Pro-Russian sources reported Ukrainian violations of the truce at Mineralne, Zhabicheve, Dokuchaievsk, Kruta Balka, Verkhnyotoretske, Spartak and Yasynuvata, in the surroundings of Donetsk city, Zaitseve, Izotove coal mine and Dolomitne, in the area of Horlivka and in the region of Mariupol, Uzhivka and Sakhanka. In the main incidents, Ukrainian troops shelled Uzhivka and Sakhanka with 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortars; 120&nbsp;mm mortar volleys also landed in Zaitseve. Dolomitne and Mineralne were meanwhile struck by 82&nbsp;mm mortars fired from Novoluhanske. BMP-1 armoured vehicles shelled Shyroka Balka and Izotove mining complex. Pro-Russian positions at Dokuchaievsk, Spartak and Yasynuvata were engaged by BMP-2 armoured vehicles.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-sahanke-stskk-4/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Саханке — СЦКК / AFU opened fire on Sakhanka — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-veli-ogon-po-neskolkim-napravleniyam-stskk/ ВСУ вели огонь по нескольким направлениям — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-krutoj-balke-stskk-3/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Крутой Балке — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-dolomitnomu-stskk-2/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Доломитному — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-verhnetoretskoe-i-dokuchaevsk-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Верхнеторецкое и Докучаевск — СЦКК ].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-sahanke-stskk-5/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Саханке — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-spartaku-stskk/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Спартаку — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-leninskomu-stskk Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по Ленинскому — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-leninskomu-i-dokuchaevsku Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по Ленинскому и Докучаевску ].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-yasinovatoj-stskk-7/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Ясиноватой — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-shahte-im-izotova-v-gorlovke-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по шахте им. Изотова в Горловке — СЦКК].</ref>

=== 15 April ===
According to the information provided by the spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters in the morning, pro-Russian troops had opened fire on 52 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--3 WIA--><ref name=MoD6am04-15>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/15/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-14-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 14 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-15 |access-date=2018-04-15 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 41 occasions in Donetsk and on 11 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=MoD_noon04-15_ua/>); the fire was returned on 19 occasions.<ref name=MoD_noon04-15_ua/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence reported at noon that two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in action and one was wounded by explosion of an unidentified explosive device in the Donbass region on 14 April.<ref name=MoD_noon04-15_ua>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/15/brifing-rechnika-ministerstva-oboroni-ukraini-shhodo-situaczii-na-linii-zitknennya/ |title=Брифінг речника Міністерства оборони України щодо ситуації на лінії зіткнення |trans-title= |date=2018-04-15 |accessdate=2018-04-15 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported 20 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 11 locations using small arms, snipers, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-20-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-predstavitelstvo-dnr-v-stskk/|title=ВСУ 20 раз нарушили режим прекращения огня — Представительство ДНР в СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-15|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-15|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Officials from the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic said that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire three times within the republic boundaries. The Ukrainian military employed small arms, heavy machine guns, grenade launchers, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and armoured fighting vehicles to attack pro-Russian positions at Kalynove, Kalynivka and Nyzhnie Lozove.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://russian.rt.com/ussr/news/503562-lnr-obstrely-ukraina|title=В ЛНР сообщили о трёх обстрелах со стороны украинских силовиков за сутки|work=RT на русском|access-date=2018-04-15|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the JFO reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 24 occasions, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1923167701027360 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 15 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=15 April 2018 |accessdate=15 April 2018 |publisher= |language=uk|website=www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts}}</ref> In the surroundings of Donetsk city, Novotroitske was hit by 120&#160;mm mortar volleys, while Pisky came under 82&#160;mm mortar fire. Rebel forces fired small arms, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers to engage Ukrainian forces at Avdiivka, Kamianka, Butivka mining complex and Verkhnyotoretske. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles shelled Pisky, and hostile sniper were active at Novotroitske. Heavy machine gun fire was reported at Opytne. Sniper fire harassed Ukrainian trops at Slavne and Berezove. In the region of Mariupol, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortar rounds landed in Pavlopil; nearby Lebedinske was also hit by 120&#160;mm mortar fire. Pyshchevik, Shyrokyne and Hnutove became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. Ukrainian positions at Talakivka were attacked by armoured fighting vehicles, while Ukrainian troops at Lebedinske came under sniper fire. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, Luhanske and Svitlodarsk were shelled with 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars. The rebels also employed 120&#160;mm mortars to pound Ukrainian positions at Troitske. Novoluhanske and Novhorodske became the target of heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles opened fire on Ukrainian redoubts at Luhanske and Troitske. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 59, one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded and another injured.<ref name=MoD6am04-16/> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city told the press that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire several times since the morning. The Ukrainian military opened fire at Dokuchaievsk, Kruta Balka, Verkhnyotoretske, Volvo Center, and Spartak, in the surroundings of Donetsk city, Shyroka Balka, Zaitseve, Dolomitne, Zheleznaya Balka and Ozeryanivka in the area of Horlivka and in the region of Mariupol, Sakhanka and Uzhivka. In the main incidents, Zaitseve, Dolomitne and Dokuchaievsk came under 120&nbsp;mm mortar fire. Sakhanka was shelled with 82&nbsp;mm mortars, BMP-1 armoured vehicles engaged pro-Russian positions at Sakhanka, Shyroka Balka and Zheleznaya Balka, which also became the target of antiaircraft guns. Some hours later, pro-Russian positions at Zheleznaya Balka were also fired at from BMP-2 armoured vehicles. An antitank guided missile was fired at Dolomitne.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-n-p-zajtsevo-dolomitnoe-i-zheleznaya-balka-stskk/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по н.п. Зайцево, Доломитному и Железной Балке — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-dokuchaevsku-stskk-6/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Докучаевску — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-krutuyu-balku-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Крутую Балку — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР]• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-kladbishhe-v-prifrontovom-zajtsevo/ ВСУ обстреляли кладбище в прифронтовом Зайцево {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/pod-obstrelom-vsu-dolomitnoe-sahanka-dokuchaevsk-stskk-2/ Под обстрелом ВСУ Доломитное, Саханка, Докучаевск — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivayut-dokuchaevsk-i-okrainy-donetska-stskk/ ВСУ обстреливают Докучаевск и окраины Донецка — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/dokuchaevsk-vnov-pod-ognem-vsu-stskk/ Докучаевск вновь под огнем ВСУ — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/pod-ognem-vsu-spartak-dokuchaevsk-i-ozeryanovka-stskk/ Под огнем ВСУ Спартак, Докучаевск и Озеряновка — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-shirokoj-balke-i-drugim-naselennym-punktam-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Широкой Балке и другим населенным пунктам — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР], 2018-04-15</ref>

=== 16 April ===
The spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 59 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--1 WIA, 1 injured--><ref name=MoD6am04-16>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/16/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-15-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 15 квітня 2018 року |trans-title=Information by ATO HQ on 15 April 2018 |date=16 April 2018 |accessdate=16 April 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 42 occasions in Donetsk region and on 17 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=MoD_1230-04-16_uk/>); the fire was returned on 24 occasions.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-16_uk/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence reported at noon that two Ukrainian servicemen were injured in the Donbass region on 15 April.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-16_uk>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/16/brifing-rechnika-ministerstva-oboroni-ukraini-shhodo-situaczii-na-linii-zitknennya/ |title=Брифінг речника Міністерства оборони України щодо ситуації на лінії зіткнення |trans-title= |date=2018-04-16 |accessdate=2018-04-16 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported 31 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 14 different locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, antiaircraft guns, antitank guided missiles, armoured personnel carriers, armoured fighting vehicles and [[T-12 antitank gun|100&nbsp;mm antitank artillery]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/iz-za-obstrelov-vsu-povrezhdeny-zhilye-doma-v-dokuchaevske-i-yasinovatoj-stskk/|title=Из-за обстрелов ВСУ повреждены жилые дома в Докучаевске и Ясиноватой — СЦКК / Houses in Dokuchayevsk and Yasinovataya were damaged by AFU shelling — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-16|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-16|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Officials from the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic recorded six Ukrainian violations of the truce within the republic's borders. Ukrainian forces engaged pro-Russian positions at Kalynyvka, Sazharivka and Lohvynove using small arms, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless guns, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, BMP-1 and BMP-2 armoured vehicles. One pro-Russian soldier was killed in action and another wounded.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/16/lnr-obstanovka-na-linii-soprikosnoveniya-za-sutki-16-04-2018/|title=ЛНР: ОБСТАНОВКА НА ЛИНИИ СОПРИКОСНОВЕНИЯ ЗА СУТКИ 16.04.2018|last=|first=|date=16 April 2018|website=News-Front|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=16 April 2018}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 22 occasions, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1924181284259335 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 16 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-16 |accessdate=2018-04-16 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> In the area of Donetsk city, rebel forces employed heavy machine guns, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars and armoured fighting vehicles to attack Ukrainian positions at Pisky. Avdiivka, Marinka, Verkhnyotoretske, Kamianka, Novotroitske and Butivka mining complex came under small arms and rocket propelled grenade fire. Ukrainian troops at Marinka were harassed with heavy machine gun fire. Small arms fire was reported at Opytne and Nevelske. In the region of Mariupol, rebel troops fired small arms, and grenade launchers at Shyrokyne, Vodiane and Hnutove. Pro-Russian armoured personnel carriers engaged Ukrainian positions at Vodiane, while armoured fighting vehicles shelled Talakivka and Hnutove. Lebedinske, Pyshchevik, Talakivka and Pavlopil came under heavy machine gun fire. Small arms fire harassed Ukrainian positions at Lebedinske, Hnutove and Talakivka. Sniper fire was reported at Shyrokyne. In the northern section of the demarcation line, heavy shelling was reported at Zaitseve, which came under 82&#160;mm mortar, 122&#160;mm and 152&#160;mm self-propelled artillery fire. Luhanske was fired at from armoured fighting vehicles, while Krymske was hit by antitank rockets. Heavy machine gun fire was recorded at Luhanske and Novoluhanske. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 52, one Ukrainian soldier (born in 1997) was killed, two servicemen and a servicewoman (nurse-anesthetist) were wounded and two soldiers injured (one of them by a [[Directed-energy weapon|laser]]).<ref name=MoD7am04-17/><ref name=MoD_noon04-17_ua/> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city reported several violations of the ceasefire throughout the day. Spartak, Dokuchaievsk, Yasynuvata and Zhabicheve, in the outskirts of Donetsk, Zaitseve, Gagarin coal mine, 6-7 coal mine, Dolomitne and Zheleznaya Balka in the area of Horlivka and Uzhivka, Petrovske, Pikuzy, [[Verhnioshyrokivske]] and Sosnovske in the region of Mariupol came under attack. In the main incidents, Dolomitne was hit by 82&nbsp;mm mortar rounds and antitank guided missiles, Uzhivka, Petrovske, Gagarin mining complex and Zaitseve were struck by 120&nbsp;mm mortar volleys; Uzhivka and Zaitseve were also shelled with 82&nbsp;mm mortars. Spartak became the target of 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles and 82&nbsp;mm mortars. BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Novotroitske opened fire on pro-Russian redoubts at Dokuchaievsk, supported by 82&nbsp;mm mortar fire. BMP-1 armoured vehicles from Dzerzhinsky engaged pro-Russian positions at Gagarin mining complex, while [[BTR-80]] armoured personnel carriers from Novhorodske attacked Zheleznaya Balka. Zhabicheve was raked by cannon fire from BMP-2 armoured vehicles. Heavy fire was reported at coal mine 6-7 later in the night, when pro-Russian redoubts in the area were engaged by Ukrainian tanks and 152&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery firing from Daliivka.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-chetyryom-napravleniyam-stskk/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по четырём направлениям — СЦКК / Engagements from the side of the AFU were recorded in four directions — JCCC].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-oktyabr-i-sosnovskoe-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Октябрь и Сосновское — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-zheleznoj-balke-stskk-2 ВСУ открыли огонь по Железной Балке — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-zajtsevo-i-kominternovo-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Зайцево и Коминтерново — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-yasinovatoj-stskk-9/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Ясиноватой — СЦКК].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-prodolzhayut-obstrel-po-n-p-petrovskoe-i-leninskoe-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Докучаевску — СЦКК / AFU opened fire on Dokuchayevsk — JCCC ].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-dokuchaevsku-stskk-7/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Докучаевску — СЦКК / AFU opened fire on Dokuchayevsk — JCCC ].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-zajtsevo-stskk-3/ ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Зайцево — СЦКК].</ref>

=== 17 April ===
According to the information provided by the spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters in the morning, pro-Russian troops had opened fire on 52 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--1 KIA,3 WIA, 2 injured--><ref name=MoD7am04-17>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/17/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-16-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 16 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-17 |access-date=2018-04-17 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 43 occasions in Donetsk and on 9 occasions in Luhansk region (including 5 times at [[Zaitseve, Luhansk Oblast|Zaitseve]])<ref name=MoD_noon04-17_ua/>); the fire was returned on 20 occasions.<ref name=MoD_noon04-17_ua/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rferl.org/a/ukraine-soldier-killed-fighting-separatists/29172133.html |title=One Ukrainian Soldier Killed Fighting Separatists |publisher=[[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty|REF/RL]] |date=17 April 2018 |accessdate=17 April 2018}}</ref> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian serviceman was killed and several others were wounded and injured in the Donbass region on 16 April. For the first time during the war a combat related injury caused by [[Directed-energy weapon|a laser weapon]] was reported.<ref name=MoD_noon04-17_ua>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/17/brifing-rechnika-ministerstva-oboroni-ukraini-shhodo-situaczii-na-linii-zitknennya/ |title=Брифінг речника Міністерства оборони України щодо ситуації на лінії зіткнення |trans-title= |date=2018-04-17 |accessdate=2018-04-17 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city recorded 35 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 17 locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, antitank guided missiles, armoured personnel carriers,&nbsp;armoured fighting vehicles, tanks and 152&nbsp;mm artillery.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-istekshie-sutki-vsu-35-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=За истекшие сутки ВСУ 35 раз нарушили режим прекращения огня — СЦКК / AFU violated the ceasefire 35 times during the past day — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-17|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-18|language=ru-RU}}</ref> One pro-Russian soldier was killed in action.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/v-rezultate-obstrela-so-storony-vsu-povrezhdeny-doma-pogib-odin-voennosluzhashhij-dnr-eduard-basurin/|title=В результате обстрела со стороны ВСУ повреждены дома, погиб один военнослужащий ДНР – Эдуард Басурин (видео) / Houses are damaged, one DPR soldier was killed because of AFU shelling — Eduard Basurin (video) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-17|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-18|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Sources from the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic said that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire five times within the republic boundaries. The Ukrainian army employed small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, rocket launchers, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, BMP-1 armoured vehicles and 152&nbsp;mm self-propelled guns to attack pro-Russian positions at Kalynivka, Lohvynove, Makarove and Kalynove.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-pyat-raz-obstrelyali-territoriyu-luganshhiny-poter-net-nm-lnr/|title=ВСУ пять раз обстреляли территорию Луганщины, потерь нет — НМ ЛНР {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-17|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-18|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/17/nochyu-po-lugansku-vsu-otkryli-ogon-nm-lnr/|title=НОЧЬЮ ПО ЛУГАНСКУ ВСУ ОТКРЫЛИ ОГОНЬ – НМ ЛНР|last=|first=|date=17 April 2018|website=News-Front|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=17 April 2018}}</ref>

The press-centre of the JFO reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 21 occasions, as a result one Ukrainian sereviceman was killed and two were wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1925240464153417 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 17 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=17 April 2018 |accessdate=17 April 2018 |publisher= |language=uk|website=www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts}}</ref> Around Donetsk city, Novotroitske was hit by rocket propelled grenades and 82&nbsp;mm mortar rounds. The rebels also fired small arms, heavy machineguns and rocket launchers at Ukrainian positions near Avdiivka, Butivka mining complex, Verkhnyotoretske and Kamianka. Heavy machine gun fire was reported at Opytne and small arms fire at Nevelske. In the region of Mariupol, pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles opened fire at Ukrainian forces at Vodiane and Pavlopil. Rebel forces attacked Vodiane and Hnutove with small arms, heavy machine guns, rocket launchers and 120&nbsp;mm mortars. Pyshchevik, Talakivka and Pavlopil became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers. Heavy machine guns were fired at Lebedinske and small arms at Shyrokyne. Hostile snipers were active at Lebedinske and Hnutove. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, Zaitseve was hit by 152&nbsp;mm artillery volleys. Ukrainian troops in the area were also harassed by sniper fire. Rebel forces shelled Troitske with 120&nbsp;mm mortars, and nearby Novooleksandrivka with rocket launchers and 82&nbsp;mm mortars. Heavy machine gun firewas reported at Luhanske. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 45 and one more Urainian serviceman was wounded.<ref name=MoD6am04-18/> Multiple ceasefire violations by Ukrainian forces were reported by pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city. The Ukrainian military opened fire at Dokuchaievsk, Yakovliivka, Zhabicheve, Spartak, Vasiilivka and Yasynuvata, in the environs of Donetsk city, Zaitseve, Dolomitne, Mayorsk checkpoint, Shyroka Balka, Dolomitne and Ozeryanivka, in the area of Horlivka, and Petrovske, Uzhivka and Pikuzy, in the region of Mariupol. In the main incidents, Ukrainian tanks engaged pro-Russian forces at Mayorsk checkpoint early in the morning, while Shyroka Balka was struck by 122&nbsp;mm artillery volleys. Nearby Zaitseve came under 120&nbsp;mm mortar fire, and antitank guided missiles were launched at Dolomitne.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-na-gorlovskom-napravlenii-stskk/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ на Горловском направлении — СЦКК / Engagements from the side of the AFU were recorded in the Gorlovka direction — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-dolomitnomu-stskk-3/ ВСУ обстреливают по н.п. Коминтерново — СЦКК (обновляется) / AFU engage Kominternovo — JCCC (being updated) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-dolomitnomu-stskk-3/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Доломитному — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivayut-po-n-p-kominternovo-stskk-obnovlyaetsya/ ВСУ обстреливают по н.п. Коминтерново — СЦКК (обновляется) / AFU engage Kominternovo — JCCC (being updated) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-zajtsevo-i-yasinovatoj-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Зайцево и Ясиноватой — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-dolomitnomu-i-ozeryanovke-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Доломитному и Озеряновке — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-petrovskomu-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Петровскому — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-n-p-spartak-i-petrovskoe-stskk/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по н.п. Спартак и Петровское — СЦКК / Attacks on Spartak and Petrovskoye from the side of the AFU were recorded — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-vasilevke-stskk-5/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Васильевке — СЦКК / AFU opened fire on Vasilievka — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-shahte-im-abakumova-vdonetske-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по шахте им. Абакумова в Донецке — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-vsu-po-leninskomu-stskk/ Зафиксирован обстрел ВСУ по Ленинскому — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-vsu-po-yakovlevke-stskk/ ВСУ продолжают обстреливать Докучаевск из БМП и гранатомета — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-zhabichevo-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Жабичево — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-prodolzhayut-obstrelivat-dokuchaevsk-iz-bmp-i-granatometa-stskk/ ВСУ продолжают обстреливать Докучаевск из БМП и гранатомета — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].</ref>

=== 18 April ===
The spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 45 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--1 KIA, 3 WIA--><ref name=MoD6am04-18>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/18/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-17-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 17 квітня 2018 року |trans-title=Information by ATO HQ on 15 April 2018 |date=18 April 2018 |accessdate=18 April 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 40 occasions in Donetsk region and on 5 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=noon04-18ru/>); the fire was returned on 22 occasions.<ref name=noon04-18ru/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian serviceman was killed and three others were wounded in action in the Donbass region on 17 April.<ref name=noon04-18ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/66202-gutsulyak-54 |title=Боевики обстреляли из тяжелой артиллерии жилые дома в Зайцево – полковник Гуцуляк |trans-title= |date=2018-04-18 |accessdate=2018-04-18 |publisher=MoD |language=ru |location=}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city recorded 27 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 14 different locations using small arms, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless guns, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, antitank guided missiles, armoured personnel carriers, armoured fighting vehicles, tanks and 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-27-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=ВСУ 27 раз нарушили режим прекращения огня — СЦКК / AFU violated the ceasefire 27 times — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-18|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-18|language=ru-RU}}</ref> The same sources reported five civilian workers from the water purification plant wounded at Yasynuvata.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-territoriyu-respubliki-po-vsem-napravleniyam-est-postradavshie-eduard-basurin/|title=ВСУ обстреляли территорию Республики по всем направлениям, есть пострадавшие – Эдуард Басурин (видео) / AFU shelled the Republic's territory in all the directions, there are victims — Eduard Basurin (video) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-18|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-18|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Local authorities in the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic said that Ukrainian forces broke the truce on four occasions within the republic borders. The Ukrainian military employed small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortars to attack pro-Russian positions at Kalynove, Kalinivka and Zholobok.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/18/lnr-obstrelyany-tri-poselka-vypushheno-110-snaryadov/|title=ЛНР: ОБСТРЕЛЯНЫ ТРИ ПОСЕЛКА, ВЫПУЩЕНО 110 СНАРЯДОВ|last=|first=|date=18 April 2018|website=News-Front|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=18 April 2018}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 20 occasions, one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1926311834046280 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 18 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-18 |accessdate=2018-04-18 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> In the surroundings of Donetsk city, rebel forces opened fire at Ukrainian troops at Nevelske, Novotroitske and Buitvka mining complex with small arms, heavy machine guns, rocket launchers, 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortars. Pisky was hit by 82&nbsp;mm mortar barrages, while antitank rockets landed in Avdiivka. Ukrainian positions at Opytne were raked by heavy machine gun fire. Small arms fire was reported at Verkhnytoretske, Marinka, Kamianka and Avdiivka. In the region of Mariupol, Nykolaevka came under 120&nbsp;mm mortar fire, while grenade launchers and 82&nbsp;mm mortars were fired at Vodiane. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles opened fire at Bohdanivka, and rocket launchers were fired at Talakivka, Hnutove and Bohdanivka. Heavy machine gun fire harassed Ukrainian troops at Talakivka and Vodiane. Lebedinske and Shyrokyne came under small arms fire. Snipers were active around Hnutove. In the northern section of the demarcation line, Popasna and Novooleksandrivka received 82&nbsp;mm mortar fire. Antitank rockets hit Ukrainian positions at Luhanske and Svitlodarsk, while heavy machine gun fire struck Novoluhanske. Ukrainian troops became the target of hostile snipers at Mayorsk and Novhoroske. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 50 and another Ukrainian soldier was injured.<ref name=MoD7am04-19/> Several Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire were reported to the press by pro-Russian authorities at evening. Yasynuvata, Volvo Center, Trudivske, Mineralne, Dokuchaievsk and Zhabicheve, in the area around Donetsk city, and in the region of Mariupol Uzhivka, Pikuzy and Dzerzhinske came under hostile fire. In the main incidents, the water purification plant at Yasynuvata, north of Donetsk city, came under heavy fire and had to be evacuated. Operations at the facilities were suspended for the next five days after the area was hit by small arms fire, machine gun fire and 82&nbsp;mm mortar rounds. Ukrainian tanks from Pisky engaged pro-Russian redoubts at Volvo Center, supported by 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortar fire. Pikuzy was struck by 120&nbsp;mm mortar volleys, an apartment building and a power line were heavily damaged. The village was left without electrical power. BMP-2 armoured vehicles opened fire at pro-Russian forces at Trudivske and Dokuchaievsk. Uzhivka, Pikuzy and Zhabicheve came under 82&nbsp;mm mortar fire.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/rabota-donetskoj-filtrovalnoj-stantsii-ostanovlena-na-pyat-dnej-stskk/ Работа Донецкой фильтровальной станции остановлена на пять дней — СЦКК / Donetsk filter station stopped its work for five days — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vedut-ogon-srazu-po-tselomu-ryadu-naselennyh-punktov-respubliki-stskk/ ВСУ ведут огонь сразу по целому ряду населенных пунктов Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-kominternovo-leninskomu-i-mineralnomu-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Коминтерново, Ленинскому и Минеральному — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/trudovskie-nahodyatsya-pod-ognem-vsu-stskk/ Трудовские находятся под огнем ВСУ — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vnov-otkryli-ogon-po-leninskomu-stskk-2/ ВСУ вновь открыли огонь по Ленинскому — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-yasinovatoj-stskk-10/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Ясиноватой — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-kominternovo-stskk-4/ ВСУ открыли огонь по Коминтерново — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР], 2018-04-18</ref>

=== 19 April ===
According to the information provided by the spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters in the morning, pro-Russian troops had opened fire on 50 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--1 WIA, 1 injured--><ref name=MoD7am04-19>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/19/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-18-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 18 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-19 |access-date=2018-04-19 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 41 occasions in Donetsk and on 9 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=MoD_noon04-19_ua/>); the fire was returned on 14 occasions.<ref name=MoD_noon04-19_ua/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded and another injured in the Donbass region on 18 April.<ref name=MoD_noon04-19_ua>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/19/brifing-rechnika-ministerstva-oboroni-ukraini-shhodo-situaczii-na-linii-zitknennya/ |title=Брифінг речника Міністерства оборони України щодо ситуації на лінії зіткнення |trans-title= |date=2018-04-19 |accessdate=2018-04-19 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city recorded 20 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 10 different locations using small arms, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers, armoured fighting vehicles and tanks.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-20-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=ВСУ 20 раз нарушили режим прекращения огня — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-19|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-19|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Sources from the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic recorded three Ukrainian violations of the truce within the republic's borders. Ukrainian forces engaged pro-Russian positions at Kalynyvka, Kalynove and Pervomaisk using 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://goves.net/news/1420-operativnaja-svodka-za-sutki-s-18-aprelja-na-19-aprelja.html|title=Оперативная сводка за сутки с 18 апреля на 19 апреля|website=Социальная сеть Новороссии|access-date=2018-04-19}}</ref>

The press-centre of the JFO reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 12 occasions, as a result one Ukrainian sereviceman was wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1927413197269477 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 19 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=19 April 2018 |accessdate=19 April 2018 |publisher= |language=uk|website=www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts}}</ref> In the surroundings of Donetsk city, Pisky was shelled with 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars. Nearby Opytne came under 120&#160;mm mortar fire, while Avdiivka was struck by 82&#160;mm mortar volleys. Rebel forces attacked Kamianka, Avdiivka and Butivka mining complex with small arms, heavy machine guns, rocket launchers. Ukrainian troops at Marinka were harassed with small arms fire. In the region of Mariupol, Ukrainian positions at Vodiane and Lebedinske were hit by small arms fire, heavy machine gun fire and antitank rockets. Small arms fire was reported at Hnutove and Pyshchevik. In the northern section of the demarcation line, antitank rockets landed in Stanytsia Luhanska, Artema and Travneve. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 35 and another Urainian soldier was wounded.<ref name=MoD6am04-20/> A number of ceasefire violations were recorded in the course of the day by pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city in several locations along the demarcation line. Volvo Center, Mykhailivka, Zhabicheve, Vasiilivka, Kruta Balka and Trudivske, in the outskirts of Donetsk city, Uzhivka, Dzerzhinske and Pikuzy, in the region of Mariupol, and Ozeryanivka, in the area of Horlivka came under fire. In the main incidents, 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortar volleys hit the industrial area of Volvo Center, while nearby Zhabicheve came under 120&nbsp;mm mortar fire. BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Marinka opened fire on pro-Russian positions at Trudivske, supported by infantry weapons. BMP-1 armoured vehicles from Talakivka shelled Pikuzy, while Uzhivka and Dzerzhinske became the target of 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles. BTR-80 armoured personnel carriers from Verkhnyotoretske engaged pro-Russian redoubts at Mykhailivka, while BMP-2 armoured vehicles and BTR-80 armoured personnel carriers from Troitske attacked Ozeryanivka. Ukrainian snipers opened fire at Marinka checkpoint, wounding three civilian commuters.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/pod-obstrelom-vsu-donetsk-i-ryad-poselkov-stskk/ Под обстрелом ВСУ Донецк и ряд поселков — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-territoriyu-respubliki-po-neskolkim-napravleniyam-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли территорию Республики по нескольким направлениям — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-prodolzhayut-obstrel-volvo-tsentra-v-kujbyshevskom-rajone-donetska-stskk/ ВСУ продолжают обстрел «Вольво-центра» в Куйбышевском районе Донецка — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-po-n-p-krutaya-balka-stskk-3/ ВСУ открыли огонь по н.п. Крутая Балка — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/ukrainskij-snajper-otkryl-ogon-po-kpvv-marinka-raneny-troe-mirnyh-zhitelya-stskk-utochneno/ Украинский снайпер открыл огонь по КПВВ «Марьинка», ранены трое мирных жителей — СЦКК (уточнено) видео {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vedut-ogon-po-mihajlovke-i-ozeryanovke-stskk/ ВСУ ведут огонь по Михайловке и Озеряновке — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-19|work=Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/utrom-zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-dvum-napravleniyam-stskk/ Утром зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по двум направлениям — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР], 2018-04-19</ref>

=== 20 April ===
The spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 35 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--2 WIA--><ref name="MoD6am04-20">{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/20/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-19-kvitnya-2018-roku/|title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 19 квітня 2018 року|last=|first=|date=20 April 2018|website=|publisher=MoD|language=uk|trans-title=Information by ATO HQ on 19 April 2018|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=20 April 2018}}</ref> (including on 32 occasions in Donetsk region and on 3 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=MoD_1230-04-20_uk/>); the fire was returned on 19 occasions.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-20_uk/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in action in the Donbass region on 19 April.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-20_uk>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/20/brifing-rechnika-ministerstva-oboroni-ukraini-shhodo-situaczii-na-linii-zitknennya/ |title=Брифінг речника Міністерства оборони України щодо ситуації на лінії зіткнення |trans-title= |date=2018-04-20 |accessdate=2018-04-20 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city recorded 18 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 13 locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, snipers, grenade launchers, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-18-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=ВСУ 18 раз нарушили режим прекращения огня — СЦКК / AFU violated the ceasefire 18 times — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-20|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-20|language=ru-RU}}</ref> The same sources denounced 78 Ukrainian violations of the truce over the past week. On the same period, the Ukrainian army fired 122&#160;mm and 152&#160;mm self-propelled artillery 77 times, 69 tank rounds and 863 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortar shells, all of them weapons banned by the Minsk agreements.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/protivnik-obstrelyal-territoriyu-respubliki-po-vsem-napravleniyam-est-ranenye-i-pogibshie-eduard-basurin/|title=Противник обстрелял территорию Республики по всем направлениям, есть раненые и погибшие – Эдуард Басурин (видео) / Adversary shelled the Republic's territory in all the directions, there are victims — Eduard Basurin (video) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-20|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-22|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Officials from the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic said that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire two times within the republic boundaries. The Ukrainian army employed small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles to attack pro-Russian positions at Prishib and Kalynove.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://goves.net/news/1442-operativnaja-svodka-za-sutki-s-19-aprelja-na-20-aprelja.html|title=Оперативная сводка за сутки с 19 апреля на 20 апреля|website=Социальная сеть Новороссии|access-date=2018-04-20}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 20 occasions, one Ukrainian serviceman was killed and another wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1928535173823946 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 20 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-20 |accessdate=2018-04-20 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.censor.net.ua/news/3062362/one_ukrainian_soldier_killed_one_injured_in_action_outside_krymske_village_today_governor_harbuz |title=One Ukrainian soldier killed, one injured in action outside Krymske village today, - Governor Harbuz|date=2018-04-20 |accessdate=2018-04-21 |website=en.censor.net.ua}}</ref> In the outskirts of Donetsk city, 120&#160;mm mortar volleys landed at Novotroitske, while Pisky and Butivka mining complex came under 82&#160;mm mortar fire. Small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers were fired at Butivka mining complex, Verkhnyotoretske, Opytne and Pisky. Small arms fire was reported at Marinka, Avdiivka, Nevelske and Novotroitske. In the region of Mariupol, pro-Russian forces fired [[BM-21 Grad|BM-21 "Grad"]] multiple rocket launchers at Ukrainian redoubts around Lebedinske; a barrage of 40 rockets struck home. Lebedinske also became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns, rocket launchers and 82&#160;mm mortars. Heavy shelling was likewise reported at Shyrokyne and Vodiane, where Ukrainian positions were pounded with 120&#160;mm mortars and 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery. Vodiane was later hit by 82&#160;mm mortar fire. Hnutove, meanwhile, was fired at from small arms, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, 122&#160;mm self-propelled guns shelled Popasna. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian positions at Krymske and Troitske, in the later case supported by 82&#160;mm mortar fire. Ukrainian troops at Zaitseve became the target of snipers and rocket launchers. Heavy machine gun fire was reported at Pervomaisk and small arms fire at Novoluhanske. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 36.<ref name=MoD7am04-21/> Pro-Russian authorities told the press that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire on several occasions throughout the day. Zhabicheve, Dokuchaievsk, Oktyabrskaya coal mine, in the area surrounding Donetsk city, Zaitseve and Holmivsky, in the area of Horlivka, and Uzhivka, Pikuzy and Bela Kamianka, in the region of Mariupol were targeted by the Ukrainian military. In the main incidents, BMP-1 armoured vehicles attacked Uzhivka, supported by 82&#160;mm mortars. Dokuchaievsk came under 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars. Oktyabrskaya coal mine was shelled with 120&#160;mm mortars, and Holmivsky with 82&#160;mm mortars. BMP-2 armoured vehicles opened fire on pro-Russian positions at Dokuchaievsk.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-neskolkim-napravleniyam-stskk/|title=Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по нескольким направлениям — СЦКК / Engagements from the side of the AFU have been recorded in several directions — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-20|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-22|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-stskk/|title=Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ — СЦКК / Engagements from the side of the AFU have been recorded — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-20|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-22|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/so-storony-vsu-zafiksirovany-obstrely-treh-napravlenij-stskk/|title=Со стороны ВСУ зафиксированы обстрелы по трем направлениям — СЦКК / Engagements from the side of the AFU have been recorded in three directions — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-20|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-22|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

=== 21 April ===
According to the information provided by the spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters in the morning, pro-Russian troops had opened fire on 36 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--1 KIA, 1 WIA--><ref name=MoD7am04-21>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/21/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-20-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 20 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-21 |access-date=2018-04-21 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 28 occasions in Donetsk and on 8 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=noon04-21ru/>); the fire was returned on 15 occasions.<ref name=noon04-21ru/> By 9:00&nbsp;am of 21 April 9 attacks on Ukrainian positions were registered.<ref name=noon04-21ru/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian serviceman was killed and another was wounded in the Donbass region on 20 April.<ref name=noon04-21ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/66316-gutsulyak-57 |title=Боевики обстреливают позиции ВСУ из "Градов" – полковник Гуцуляк |trans-title= |date=2018-04-21 |accessdate=2018-04-21 |publisher=MoD |language=ru|quote=«Вчера утром, около 06.00, враг применил по украинским защитникам населенного пункта Лебединский РСЗО БМ-21 «Град». Выпустили 40 реактивных снарядов. Обстрел велся со стороны оккупированного села Саханка», – рассказал он.}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city reported 22 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 12 locations using small arms, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-sutki-vsu-primenili-po-territorii-respubliki-285-boepripasov-stskk/|title=За сутки ВСУ применили по территории Республики 285 боеприпасов — СЦКК / AFU fired 285 rounds on the Republic's territory during the day — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-21|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-21|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Local sources told the press that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire on five occasions within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, rocket launchers and BMP-1 armoured vehicles to attack pro-Russian positions at Zeleznaya Roshcha, Kalynove, Nyzhne Lozove and Knyaz Igor memorial.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://goves.net/news/1453-operativnaja-svodka-za-sutki-s-20-aprelja-na-21-aprelja.html|title=Оперативная сводка за сутки с 20 апреля на 21 апреля|website=Социальная сеть Новороссии|access-date=2018-04-21}}</ref>

The press-centre of the JFO reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 31 occasions. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 47, one Ukrainian serviceman was killed, two were wounded and two injured.<ref name=MoD6am04-22/> In the environs of Donetsk city, Novotroitske was shelled with 120&#160;mm mortars, while Avdiivka and Nevelske were attacked with small arms and rocket launchers. Heavy machine gun and sniper fire was reported at Novotroitske. Ukrainian personnel at Krasnohorivka and Butivka mining complex. Pro-Russian tanks engaged Ukrainian redoubts at Pavlopil and Pyshchevik, in the region of Mariupol. In the same area, 120&#160;mm mortar barrages hit Vodiane, and armoured fighting vehicles opened fire at Pavlopil and Talakivka. Rebel troops fired small arms and rocket launchers at Hnutove and Vodiane, and heavy machine guns at Pyshchevik, Talakivka and Chernenko. Ukrainian forces were harassed with small arms at Lebedinske and sniper fire at Pavlopil. In the northern section of the demarcation line, Zaitseve, Katerinivka, and Novooleksandrivka came under 120&#160;mm mortar fire, while Novoselivka, Luhanske, Novhorodske, and Zaitseve were shelled with 82&#160;mm mortars. Zaitseve was also hit by antitank rockets. Ukrainian troops at Krymske became the target of small arms and grenade launchers, Small arms fire was likewise reported at Novoselivka. As a result, one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded and another soldier had suffered combat related injuries.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1929742467036550 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 21 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=21 April 2018 |accessdate=21 April 2018 |publisher= |language=uk|website=www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city reported a number of Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire by evening. The Ukrainian military opened fire at pro-Russian forces at Dokuchaievsk, Kruta Balka, Zhabicheve, Mykhailivka, Abakumove, Spartak, Trudivske and Staromyhailivka, in the area of Donetsk city, Ozeryanivka, Dolomitne and Zaitseve in the area of Horlivka and in the region of Mariupol Sosnovske, Pikuzy and Dzerzhinske. In the main incidents, Ukrainian forces at Dokuchaievsk were engaged with automatic grenade launchers, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars and BMP-2 armoured vehicles. Zhabicheve, Dzerzhinske, Pikuzy and Abakumove came under 82&#160;mm mortar fire. Later, 120&#160;mm mortar volleys landed in Pikuzy and Ozeryanivka.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-prodolzhayut-obstrel-naselennyh-punktov-respubliki-stskk/|title=ВСУ продолжают обстрел населенных пунктов Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-22|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-22|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryvali-ogon-po-ryadu-naselennyh-punktov-respubliki-stskk/|title=ВСУ открывали огонь по ряду населенных пунктов Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-21|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-22|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivali-dokuchaevsk-i-kominternovo-iz-minometov-stskk/|title=ВСУ обстреливали Докучаевск и Коминтерново из минометов — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-21|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-22|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-neskolkim-napravleniyam-stskk-2/|title=Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по нескольким направлениям — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-21|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-22|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Colonel Andryi Marochko, military spokesman of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic, announced that pro-Russian forces shot down an armed Ukrainian drone over the city of [[Luhansk]], the second since 1 April.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/21/narodnaya-militsiya-lnr-sbila-bespilotnik-s-boevym-zaryadom-vozle-luganska/|title=НАРОДНАЯ МИЛИЦИЯ ЛНР СБИЛА БЕСПИЛОТНИК С БОЕВЫМ ЗАРЯДОМ|last=|first=|date=21 April 2018|website=News-Front|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=21 April 2018}}</ref>

=== 22 April ===
The spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 47 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--1 KIA, 2 WIA, 2 injured--><ref name=MoD6am04-22>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/22/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-21-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 21 квітня 2018 року |trans-title=Information by ATO HQ on 21 April 2018 |date=22 April 2018 |accessdate=22 April 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk|quote=...на жаль, один захисник України загинув. Двоє наших воїнів — зазнали поранень. Ще два українські військовослужбовці — отримали бойове травмування}}</ref> (including on 36 occasions in Donetsk region and on 11 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=MoD_1230-04-22_uk/>); the fire was returned on 20 occasions.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-22_uk/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian soldier was killed, two others were wounded and another two were injured in action in the Donbass region on 21 April.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-22_uk>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/22/brifing-rechnika-ministerstva-oboroni-ukraini-shhodo-situaczii-na-linii-zitknennya/ |title=Брифінг речника Міністерства оборони України щодо ситуації на лінії зіткнення |trans-title= |date=2018-04-22 |accessdate=2018-04-22 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources at Donetsk city recorded 36 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 18 different locations using small arms,heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-razrushili-doma-na-territorii-respubliki-stskk/|title=ВСУ разрушили дома на территории Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-22|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-22|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Officials from the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic said that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire four times within the republic boundaries. The Ukrainian army employed small arms, rocket launchers, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars to attack pro-Russian positions at Zholobok, Pervomaisk and Kalynove-Borshchevate.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://ria.ru/world/20180422/1519153565.html|title=Силовики четыре раза за сутки нарушили перемирие, заявили в ЛНР|date=2018-04-22|work=РИА Новости|access-date=2018-04-22|language=ru}}</ref> The same sources said that one civilian resident was killed by an explosive device at Vrubivskyi, in [[Lutuhyne Raion]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/22/v-lnr-soobshhili-chto-mirnyj-zhitel-pogib-pri-vzryve-boepripasa/|title=В ЛНР сообщили, что мирный житель погиб при взрыве боеприпаса|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-04-22|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 10 occasions, with no accompanying casualties on the Ukrainian side.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1930852496925547 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 22 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-22 |accessdate=2018-04-22 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> In the area around Donetsk city, small arms and rocket launchers were fired at Avdiivka, Butivka mining complex and Marinka. Heavy machine gun fire was reported at Krasnohorivka and small arms fire at Kamianka. Ukrainian troops at Novotroitske came under sniper fire. In the region of Mariupol, rebel forces opened fire on Ukrainian positions at Talakivka with small arms, heavy machine guns, grenade launchers and 82&#160;mm mortars. Vodiane was hit by small arms fire and antitank rockets, while heavy machine guns were fired at Pavlopil, Hnutove and Shyrokyne. Sniper fire was reported at Pavlopil. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, 120&#160;mm mortar volleys landed in Nohorodske and Luhanske. The separatists also fired 82&#160;mm mortars at Novoselivka, Novhorodske and Troitske. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles shelled Luhanske and Troitske. Heavy machine gun fire struck Ukrainian positions at Troitske, Luhanske and Novoselivka. Ukrainian troops at Novhorodske became the target of small arms. By the end of the day, the number of incidents had risen to 30.<ref name=":7" /> A number of Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire were reported throughout the day by pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city. Dokuchaievsk, Vasiliivka, Yasynuvata, Yakovliivka, Trudivske, Verkhnyotoretske, Kruta Balka, Mineralne and Mykhailivka, in the outskirts of Donetsk city, Ozeryanivka, Dolomitne, Zaitseve and Shyroka Balka in the area of Horlivka and in the region of Mariupol, Sosnovske and Dzerzhinske were fired at from Ukrainian positions. In the main incidents, Ukrainian forces shelled Ozeryanivka and Yasynuvata with 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars. Dokuchaievsk and Kruta Balka came under 120&#160;mm mortar fire, while 82&#160;mm mortar rounds landed in Dzerzhinske and Shyroka Balka. BMP-2 armoured vehicles engaged pro-Russian positions at Dokuchaievsk, Mykhailivka and Ozeryanivka.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivayut-poselki-u-linii-soprikosnoveniya-i-dfs-stskk/ ВСУ обстреливают поселки у линии соприкосновения и ДФС — СЦКК | Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivayut-dzerzhinskoe-verhnetoretskoe-nizhnee-i-yasinovatuyu-stskk/ ВСУ обстреливают Дзержинское, Верхнеторецкое Нижнее и Ясиноватую — СЦКК | Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivayut-dokuchaevsk-stskk/ ВСУ обстреливают Докучаевск — СЦКК | Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-aktivno-otkryvayut-ogon-v-tom-chisle-po-dfs-stskk/ ВСУ активно открывают огонь, в том числе по ДФС — СЦКК | Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-mihajlovku-dolomitnoe-ozeryanovku-i-dzerzhinskoe-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Михайловку, Доломитное, Озеряновку и Дзержинское — СЦКК | Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/pod-ognem-vsu-yasinovataya-krutaya-balka-i-yakovlevka-stskk/ Под огнем ВСУ Ясиноватая, Крутая Балка и Яковлевка — СЦКК | Официальный сайт ДНР], 2018-04-23.</ref>

=== 23 April ===
According to the information provided by the spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters in the morning, pro-Russian troops had opened fire on 30 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--no casualties--><ref name=":7">{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/23/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-22-kvitnya-2018/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 22 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-23 |access-date=2018-04-23 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 25 occasions in Donetsk and on 5 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=MoD_noon04-23_ua/>); the fire was returned on 20 occasions.<ref name=MoD_noon04-23_ua/> By 9:00&nbsp;am of 23 April 10 attacks on Ukrainian positions were recorded.<ref name=MoD_noon04-23_ua/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence reported at noon no casualties in the Donbass region on 22 April.<ref name=MoD_noon04-23_ua>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/23/brifing-rechnika-ministerstva-oboroni-ukraini-shhodo-situaczii-na-linii-zitknennya/ |title=Брифінг речника Міністерства оборони України щодо ситуації на лінії зіткнення |trans-title= |date=2018-04-23 |accessdate=2018-04-23 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city recorded 32 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 17 locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, grenade launchers, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-32-raza-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=ВСУ 32 раза нарушили режим прекращения огня — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-23|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-23|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Four days after being attacked with mortar fire, Yasynuvata's water purification plant resumed operations as usual.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dan-news.info/defence/pervaya-noch-raboty-dfs-posle-chetyrexdnevnogo-prostoya-proshla-spokoj