The press-centre of the JFO reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 25 occasions, as a result three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1931894620154668 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 23 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=23 April 2018 |accessdate=23 April 2018 |publisher= |language=uk|website=www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts}}</ref> By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 44, one more Ukrainian serviceman was wounded and one was injured. In the outskirts of Donetsk city, Butivka mining complex was targeted by 82&nbsp;mm mortars. Separatist forces opened fire on Avdiivka, Verkhnyotoretske, Kamianka, Krasnohorivka, Marinka, Nevelske and Butivkamining complex using small arms, heavy machine guns, grenade launchers and armoured fighting vehicles. In the region of Mariupol, Vodiane was hit by 120&nbsp;mm mortars, while 82&nbsp;mm mortar volleys struck Lebedinske. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged pro-Russian positions at Vodiane, Hnutove, Lebedinske, Pavlopil, Pyshchevik and Talakivka supported by infantry weaponsand rocket launchers. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, Troitske was shelled with 82&nbsp;mm and 120&nbsp;mm mortars; 82&nbsp;mm mortar rounds also landed in Novooleksandrivka. Novozvanivka, Popasna, Troitske and Novoselivka became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns and grenade launchers.<ref name=MoD6am04-24/> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city told the press that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire several times in the course of the day. Yasynuvata, Dokuchaievsk, Staromykhailivka, Mykhailivka, Volvo Center and Spartak, in the surroundings of Donetsk city, Sakhanka, Uzhivka, Styla and Pikuzy in the region of Mariupol, and in the area of Horlivka, Zaitseve and Shyroka Balka came under attack. In the main incidents, Dokuchaievsk became the target of 120&#160;mm mortars and antitank guided missiles; a farm complex was damaged. Heavy shelling was meanwhile reported at Uzhivka, shelled with 120&#160;mm mortars and 152&#160;mm self-propelled artillery firing from Vodiane. Zaitseve, Yasynuvata, Uzhivka, Pikuzy, Sakhanka and Styla came under 82&#160;mm mortar fire. BMP-1 armoured vehicles opened fire at pro-Russian positions at Pikuzy, Spartak, Sakhanka, Styla and Shyroka Balka. BMP-2 armoured vehicles attacked Yasynuvata and Zaitseve. Pro-Russian forces at Mykhailivka were engaged by BTR-80 armoured personnel carriers from Verkhnyotoretske, supported by 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles and heavy small arms fire.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vedut-obstrel-naselennyh-punktov-respubliki-stskk/ ВСУ ведут обстрел населенных пунктов Республики — СЦКК / AFU shell populated localities of the Republic — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-dvum-napravleniyam/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по двум направлениям {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-dvum-napravleniyam-stskk/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по двум направлениям — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-dvum-napravleniyam-stskk-2/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по двум направлениям — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivayut-leninskoe-i-spartak-stskk/ ВСУ обстреливают Ленинское и Спартак — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vedut-massirovannyj-obstrel-respubliki-stskk/ ВСУ ведут массированный обстрел Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vedut-ogon-po-petrovskomu-rajonu-donetska-stskk/ ВСУ ведут огонь по Петровскому району Донецка — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].</ref><ref name=":8" />

=== 24 April ===
The spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 44 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--4 WIA, 1 injured--><ref name=MoD6am04-24>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/24/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-23-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 23 квітня 2018 року |trans-title=Information by ATO HQ on 23 April 2018 |date=24 April 2018 |accessdate=24 April 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 34 occasions in Donetsk region and on 10 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=noon04-24ru/>); the fire was returned on 23 occasions.<ref name=noon04-24ru/> By 9:00&nbsp;am of 24 April 13 ceasefire violations were registered.<ref name=noon04-24ru/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence reported at noon that two Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in action and three others were injured by explosion of an unidentified explosive device in the Donbass region on 23 April.<ref name=noon04-24ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/66385-prauta-14 |title=Вчера боевики 44 раза прицельно обстреляли украинские позиции – полковник Праута |trans-title= |date=2018-04-24 |accessdate=2018-04-24 |publisher=MoD |language=ru |location=}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city recorded 20 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 13 different locations using small arms, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, antitank guided missiles, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles. One civilian resident was killed and another wounded at Zaitseve.<ref name=":8">{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-25-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=ВСУ 25 раз нарушили режим прекращения огня — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-24|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-25|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Local authorities in the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic said that Ukrainian forces broke the truce on six occasions within the republic borders. The Ukrainian military employed small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless guns, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars to attack pro-Russian positions at Kalynove, Kalinivka, Stepove and Pervomaisk.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/24/lnr-operativnaya-svodka-obstrelyany-chetyre-poselka-2/|title=ЛНР: оперативная сводка – обстреляны четыре поселка|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-04-25|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 28 occasions, four Ukrainian servicemen were wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1932952493382214 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 24 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-24 |accessdate=2018-04-24 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> In the area around Donetsk city, Novotroitske was hit by 120&#160;mm mortar barrages. Rocket propelled grenades landed in Avdiivka and Marinka, and heavy machine gun fire was reported at Pervomaisk, Krasnohorivka and Butivka mining complex. Ukrainian troops at Kamianka, Novomykhailivka and Avdiivka were harassed with small arms fire. In the region of Mariupol, heavy shelling was reported at Lomakine, which became the target of antitank rockets, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars and 122&#160;mm self-prpeled artillery. Hnutove and Pyshchevik came under 120&#160;mm mortar fire, and 82&#160;mm mortar volleys struck Shyrokyne and Vodiane. Rocket launchers were fired at Hnutove, Talakivka, Lebedinske and Pyshchevik. Ukrainian positions at Pavlopil were raked with heavy machine gun fire, while armoured fighting vehicles attacked Vodiane, Hnutove and Pyshchevik. Small arms fire was reported at Vodiane and Talakivka, and sniper activity at Pavlopil, Talakivka and Shyrokyne. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 69, five more Ukrainian soldiers were wounded and two were injured.<ref name=MoD7am04-25/> Pro-Russian sources told the press that Ukrainian forces opened fire at pro-Russian positions on several occasions throughout the day. The Ukrainian army attacked Trudivske, Kruta Balka, Dokuchaievsk, Verkhnyotoretske and Yasynuvata, in the environs of Donetsk city, Zaitseve, Ozeryanivka, Izotove coal mine and Dolomitne, in the area of Horlivka, and in the region of Mariupol, Sakhanka, Verhnioshyrokivske, Uzhivka, Dzerzhinske and Zaichenko. In the main incidents, Sakhanka, Uzhivka, Trudivske, Verhnioshyrokivske and Dolomitne came under 120&#160;mm mortar fire. Ukrainian troops shelled Pikuzy, Uzhivka, Trudivske, Yasynuvata, Dokuchaievsk and Zaichenko with 82&#160;mm mortars. BMP-1 armoured vehicles engaged pro-Russian redoubts at Zaitseve, Trudivske and Uzhivka, while BMP-2 armoured vehicles opened fire at Verhnioshyrokivske, Pikuzy, Trudivske, Volvo Center and Zaichenko. Pro-Russian forces at Pikuzy became the target of antiaircraft guns.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-prodolzhayut-obstrel-poselkov-respubliki-stskk/ ВСУ продолжают обстрел поселков Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryvali-ogon-po-naselennym-punktam-respubliki-stskk/ ВСУ открывали огонь по населенным пунктам Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР]<br />•  [https://dnr-online.ru/nochyu-zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-trem-napravleniyam-stskk/ Ночью зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по трем направлениям — СЦКК / At night AFU shelling were recorded in three directions — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/pod-obstrel-vsu-popali-ozeryanovka-dokuchaevsk-i-trudovskie-stskk/ Под обстрел ВСУ попали Озеряновка, Докучаевск и Трудовские — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryvali-ogon-po-naselennym-punktam-respubliki-stskk/ ВСУ открывали огонь по населенным пунктам Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-neskolkim-napravleniyam-stskk-3/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по нескольким направлениям — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР], 2018-04-24.</ref>

=== 25 April ===
According to the information provided by the spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters in the morning, pro-Russian troops had opened fire on 69 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--9 WIA, 2 injured--><ref name=MoD7am04-25>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/25/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-24-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 24 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-25 |access-date=2018-04-25 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 49 occasions in Donetsk and on 20 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=MoD_noon04-25_ua/>); the fire was returned on 30 occasions.<ref name=MoD_noon04-25_ua/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that seven Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in action, two were injured in a combat related situation, and two were wounded by explosion of an [[Improvised explosive device|IED]] the Donbass region on 24 April.<ref name=MoD_noon04-25_ua>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/25/brifing-rechnika-ministerstva-oboroni-ukraini-shhodo-situaczii-na-linii-zitknennya/ |title=Брифінг речника Міністерства оборони України щодо ситуації на лінії зіткнення |trans-title= |date=2018-04-25 |accessdate=2018-04-25 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city recorded 43 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 21 locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, antiaircraft guns, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-43-raza-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=ВСУ 43 раза нарушили режим прекращения огня — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-25|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-26|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local sources, the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire 12 times within the borders of the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed sniper rifles, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, BMP-1 armoured vehicles and 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery to engage pro-Russian positions at Kalynivka, Lohvynove, Nyzhnie Lozove, Zholobok and Knyaz Igor memorial.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/25/lnr-operativnaya-svodka-obstrelyany-shest-naselennyh-punktov-4/|title=ЛНР: оперативная сводка – обстреляны шесть населенных пунктов|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-04-26|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the JFO reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 33 occasions, as a result four Ukrainian servicemen were wounded and one soldier was injured.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1934052033272260 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 25 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=25 April 2018 |accessdate=25 April 2018 |publisher= |language=uk|website=www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts}}</ref> In the area of Donetsk city, rebel forces fired rocket propelled grenades and 120&#160;mm mortars at Ukrainian positions at Verkhnyotoretske and Butivka mining complex. Avdiivka became the target of small arms, rocket launchers and 82&#160;mm mortars. Armoured fighting vehicles attacked Butivka mining complex, while nearby Kamianka was hit by antitank rockets. Heavy machine gun fire was reported at Krasnohorivka, Nevelske, Slavne, Verkhnyotoretske and Pisky. In the region of Mariupol, Hnutove was struck by small arms fire, heavy machine gun fire, antitank rockets, antitank guided missiles and 120&#160;mm mortar rounds. Antitank guided missiles also hit Talakivka. Armoured fighting vehicles opened fire at Talakivka and Bohdanivka. Heavy machine gun fire was reported at Pavlopil, and small arms fire at Shyrokyne, Lebedinske and Pyshchevik. In the northern section of the demarcation line, the village of Novoluhanske witnesses heavy shelling. The Ukrainian stronghold was pounded by 120&#160;mm mortars, tanks, 152&#160;mm artillery and BM-21 "Grad" multiple rocket launchers. Nearby Svitlodarsk was shelled by 82&#160;mm mortars and 152&#160;mm self-propelled guns. Pro-Russian tanks engaged Ukrainian positions at Novoselivka, supported by small arms, grenade launchers, 82&#160;mm mortars and armoured fighting vehicles. Novozvanivka, meanwhile, was fired at from heavy machine guns, rocket launchers, 120&#160;mm mortars and armoured fighting vehicles. Troitske came under 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortar fire, and 122&#160;mm artillery volleys hit Zaitseve. Armoured fighting vehicles opened fire on Ukrainian positions at Luhanske and Novhorodske supported by 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars and 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery. Ukrainian troops at Malinove were harassed with small arms fire. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 76, four more Ukrainian servicemen were wounded and two more injured.<ref name=MoD6am04-26/> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city told the press that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire several times throughout the day. Spartak, Yasinuvata, Yakovliivka, Trudivske, Mineralne and Verkhnyotoretske, in the outskirts of Donetsk city, Zaitseve, Holmivsky and Dolomitne, in the area of Horlivka, and in the region of Mariupol, Uzhivka, Styla and Pikuzy. In the main incidents, heavy shelling was reported at Zaitseve, where three civilian residences were wrecked by 120&#160;mm mortar barrages. The Ukrainian military also employed 120&#160;mm mortars to shell Spartak, Mineralne, Styla, Pikuzy, <!-- Official report mistakes Pikuzy (Mariupol region) for Yakovliivka (Donetsk city) -->Uzhivka and Holmivsky. Later in the evening, Ukrainian tanks engaged pro-Russian positions at Spartak. Yakovlivka, Spartak, Yasynuvata and Mineralne came under 82&#160;mm mortar fire. Zaitseve and Ozeryanivka were hit by 100&#160;mm T-12 antitank artillery. Self-propelled 122&#160;mm guns shelled Zaitseve, while BMP-1 armoured vehicles opened fire on pro-Russian forces at Dolomitne, Ozeryanivka, Styla, Spartak, coal min 6/7 and [[Trudivske]], while BMP-2 armoured vehicles fired at Styla on two different occasions, once at Ozeryanivka and Novolaspa. BTR-80 armoured personnel carriers attacked Ozeryanivka, and antitank guided missiles landed in the surroundings of Zaitseve.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/v-rezultate-obstrela-so-storony-vsu-razrusheny-tri-doma-v-zajtsevo/ В результате обстрела со стороны ВСУ разрушены три дома в Зайцево {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/pod-obstrelom-vsu-chast-zajtsevo-styla-spartak-i-yasinovataya-stskk/ Под обстрелом ВСУ часть Зайцево, Стыла, Спартак и Ясиноватая — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-25|work=Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/nochyu-i-utrom-vsu-prodolzhali-obstrely-territorii-respubliki-stskk/ Ночью и утром ВСУ продолжали обстрелы территории Республики — СЦКК / AFU kept shelling the Republic's territory at night and in the morning — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/pod-obstrelom-vsu-kominternovo-i-verhnetoretskoe-nizhnee-stskk/ Под обстрелом ВСУ — Коминтерново и Верхнеторецкое нижнее — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-trem-napravleniyam-stskk-2/ Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по трем направлениям — СЦКК / Engagements from the side of the AFU were recorded in three directions — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vnov-zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-trem-napravleniyam-stskk/ Вновь зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по трем направлениям — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vecherom-i-nochyu-vsu-obstrelivali-naselennye-punkty-respubliki-stskk/ Вечером и ночью ВСУ обстреливали населенные пункты Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР], 2018-04-26</ref>

=== 26 April ===
The spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 76 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--8 WIA, 3 injured--><ref name=MoD6am04-26>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/26/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-25-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 25 квітня 2018 року |trans-title=Information by ATO HQ on 25 April 2018 |date=26 April 2018 |accessdate=26 April 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 51 occasions in Donetsk region and on 25 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=noon04-26ru/>); the fire was returned on 30 occasions.<ref name=noon04-26ru/> By 9:00&nbsp;am of 26 April 6 ceasefire violations were registered, exclusively in Donetsk region.<ref name=noon04-26ru/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that eight Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in action and two soldiers were injured in the Donbass region on 25 April.<ref name=noon04-26ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/66438-prauta-16 |title=Боевики стреляют из "Градов", танков, тяжелой артиллерии и минометов – полковник Праута |trans-title= |date=2018-04-26 |accessdate=2018-04-26 |publisher=MoD |language=ru |location=}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city recorded 38 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 18 locations using small arms, snipers, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&nbsp;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&nbsp;mm mortars, 120&nbsp;mm mortars, antiaircraft guns, armoured personnel carriers, armoured fighting vehicles, 100&#160;mm antitank guns, tanks and 122&nbsp;mm self-propelled artillery.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-38-raz-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-stskk/|title=ВСУ 38 раз нарушили режим прекращения огня — СЦКК / AFU violated ceasefire 38 times — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-26|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-26|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local sources, the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire within the boundaries of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic. The Ukrainian military employed small arms, heavy machine guns, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars and 120&#160;mm mortars to pound pro-Russian redoubts at Kalynivka, Kalynove, Lohvynove and Nyzhnie Lozove.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/26/lnr-obstanovka-na-linii-soprikosnoveniya-karta-obstrelov-26-aprelya-2018/|title=ЛНР: Обстановка на линии соприкосновения. Карта обстрелов 26 апреля 2018|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-04-27|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 21 occasions, four Ukrainian servicemen were wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1935085793168884 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 26 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-26 |accessdate=2018-04-26 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> In the surroundings of Donetsk city, pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian positions at Novotroitske supported by small arms, rocket launchers and 120&#160;mm mortars. Krasnohorivka, Butivka mining complex and Verkhnyotoretske were hit by heavy machine gun fire, rocket launchers and 82&#160;mm mortar rounds. The separatists fired small arms and rocket propelled grenades at Avdiivka, Marinka and Kamianka. Butivka mining complex was shelled by armoured fighting vehicles, while Nevelske and Opytne became the target of heavy machine guns. Opytne also came under small arms fire. In the region of Mariupol, Ukrainian positions at Lebedinske were hit by small arms fire, heavy machine gun fire and 82&#160;mm mortar volleys. Rebel troops fired small arms and grenade launchers at the Ukrainian troops of Marinka. Ukrainian forces at Talakivka were harassed with heavy machine gun fire, and small arms fire was reported at Lomakine, Lebedinske, Shyrokyne, Hnutove and Pyschevik. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, Ukrainian positions at Zaitseve were hit by heavy machine guns, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles and 120&#160;mm mortars. Rebel forces fired small arms, heavy machine guns, rocket propelled grenades and 82&#160;mm mortars at Ukrainian redoubts near Zolote. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 52, total five Ukrainian soldiers were wounded and injured.<ref name=MoD7am04-27/> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city told the press that Ukrainian forces broke the truce several times since the morning. The Ukrainian military opened fire at Yasynuvata, Mykhailivka, Dokuchaievsk and Spartak, in the surroundings of Donetsk, Zaitseve, Holmivsky and Ozeryanivka, in the area of Horlivka, and in the region of Mariupol, Sakhanka, Pikuzy and Novolaspa. In the main incidents, Zaitseve became the target of a vicious shelling, when pro-Russian positions in the area were engaged by automatic grenade launchers, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, antiaircraft guns, BMP-2 armoured vehicles and tanks. Dokuchaievsk was hit by 152&#160;mm self-propelled artillery, while 122&#160;mm artillery volleys landed in Holmivsky. The Ukrainian military fired 120&#160;mm mortars at Mykhailivka, Mineralne, Dokuchaievsk and Yasynuvata, and 82&#160;mm mortars at Yasynuvata, Spartak and Mineralne. Ukrainian tanks engaged pro-Russian redoubts at Dokuchaievsk, and BMP-1 armoured vehicles attacked Yasynuvata and Pikuzy. BMP-2 opened 30&#160;mm cannon fire at Spartak, Dokuchaievsk, Novolaspa, Ozeryanivka and Mineralne. Two elderly civilian residents were killed at Dokuchaievsk.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/utrom-zafiksirovany-ocherednye-obstrely-so-storoony-vsu-stskk/|title=Утром зафиксированы очередные обстрелы со сторооны ВСУ — СЦКК / More shelling from the side of the AFU was recorded in the morning — JCCC {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-26|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-27|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/v-pervoj-polovine-dnya-zafiksirovany-ocherednye-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-stskk/|title=В первой половине дня зафиксированы очередные обстрелы со стороны ВСУ — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-26|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-27|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-chetyrem-napravleniyam-stskk-2/|title=Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по четырем направлениям — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-26|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-27|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/dvoe-mirnyh-zhitelej-pogiblo-v-rezultate-obstrela-vsu-dokuchaevska-stskk/|title=Двое мирных жителей погибли в результате обстрела ВСУ Докучаевска — СЦКК (видео) / Two civilians were killed in shelling of Dokuchayevsk — JCCC (video) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-26|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-27|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelivali-naselennye-punkty-respubliki-iz-minometov-granatometov-i-bmp-stskk/|title=ВСУ обстреливали населенные пункты Республики из минометов, гранатометов и БМП — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-26|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-27|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

=== 27 April ===
According to the information provided by the spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters in the morning, pro-Russian troops had opened fire on 52 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--3 WIA, 2 injured--><ref name=MoD7am04-27>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/27/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-26-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 26 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-27 |access-date=2018-04-27 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 49 occasions in Donetsk and on 3 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=noon04-27ru/>); the fire was returned on 30 occasions.<ref name=noon04-27ru/> From the midnight of 27 April till noon 12 ceasefire violations were registered in Donetsk region and 1 in Luhansk region.<ref name=noon04-27ru/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded and two were injured in the Donbass region on 26 April.<ref name=noon04-27ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/66472-prauta-17 |title=Вчера боевики 52 раза обстреляли украинские позиции – полковник Праута |trans-title= |date=2018-04-27 |accessdate=2018-04-27 |publisher=MoD |language=ru}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city recorded 35 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 14 different areas using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, antiaircraft guns, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers, armoured fighting vehicles, tanks, 122&#160;mm and 152&#160;mm self-propelled artillery.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-35-raz-obstrelyali-territoriyu-respubliki-stskk/|title=ВСУ 35 раз обстреляли территорию Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-27|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-27|language=ru-RU}}</ref> The same sources recorded 231 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in the course of the past week. The Ukrainian army fired 77 artillery rounds, 19 tank rounds, and 1,264 shells from 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dan-news.info/defence/komandovanie-dnr-zayavilo-o-svyshe-230-narusheniyax-rezhima-tishiny-so-storony-vsu-za-nedelyu.html|title=Командование ДНР заявило о свыше 230 нарушениях режима тишины со стороны ВСУ за неделю {{!}} ДАН|website=dan-news.info|language=ru-RU|access-date=2018-04-29}}</ref> Authorities from the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic said that the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire two times within the republic boundaries. Ukrainian forces from Luhanske employed small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers and 82&#160;mm mortars to attack pro-Russian positions at Lozove.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/27/vsu-dvazhdy-obstrelyali-territoriyu-lnr-za-minuvshie-sutki/|title=ВСУ дважды обстреляли территорию ЛНР за минувшие сутки|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-04-28|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The press-centre of the JFO reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 26 occasions, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1936157213061742 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 27 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=27 April 2018 |accessdate=27 April 2018 |publisher= |language=uk|website=www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts}}</ref> In the surroundings of Donetsk city, rebel troops fired infantry weapons and rocket launchers at the Ukrainian strongholds of Nevelske, Pisky, Marinka, Kamianka and Butivka mining complex. Antitank rockets landed around Avdiivka, while Ukrainian forces at Verkhnyotoretske and Opytne came under heavy machine gun fire. Small arms fire was reported at Avdiivka and Krasnohorivka, and snipers harassed Ukrainian troops at Marinka. In the region of Mariupol, Vodiane was attacked with small arms, heavy machine guns, grenade lanchers, 82&#160;mm mortars and 120&#160;mm mortars. Nearby Lebedinske was struck by 120&#160;mm mortar volleys. The separatists also fired small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers at Lebedinske and Hnutove. Armoured fighting vehicles shelled Talakivka, which also became the target of antitank guided missiles. Rocket propelled grenades were fired at Vodiane, and heavy machine gun fire raked Ukrainian redoubts at Shyrokyne, Pavlopil and Pyshchevik. Small arms fire was reported at Talakivka and Shyrokyne. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, Ukrainian armoured fighting vehicles engaged Ukrainian positions at Krymske supported by heavy machine guns, rocket launchers, 82&#160;mm mortars and 120&#160;mm mortars. Armoured fighting vehicles also attacked Svitlodarsk. Simultaneously, Ukrainian positions there received 120&#160;mm mortar fire. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 53 and three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded.<ref name=MoD6am04-28/> Donetsk People's Republic deputy ministry of defence, Eduard Basurin, told the press that early in the morning, a team of 14 Ukrainian marines attempted to break through the demarcation line in the region of Mariupol. The intruders end up stranded in a minefield and came under fire from pro-Russian positions. The Ukrainian marines managed to got back to their lines supported by mortar fire. Basurin claimed that three Ukrainian servicemen were killed and four others wounded. Two pro-Russian soldiers were killed in action.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/otbita-ataka-na-pozitsii-vs-dnr-na-mariupolskom-napravlenii-basurin/|title=Отбита атака на позиции ВС ДНР на Мариупольском направлении — Эдуард Басурин (видео) / Attack on positions of the DPR Armed Forces in the Mariupol direction was repelled — Eduard Basurin (video) {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-27|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-28|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Pro-Russian sources also reported a number of Ukrainian violations of the truce at Yasynuvata, Spartak, Kruta Balka and Vasiliivka, in the area of Donetsk city, and Novolaspa, Verkhnyoshyrokivske, Petrovske, Dzerzhinske and Pikuzy, in the region of Mariupol. In the main incidents, Verkhnyoshyrokivske came under 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars; 120&#160;mm mortar volleys also struck Spartak, and Pikuzy. BMP-2 armoured vehicles opened fire on pro-Russian positions at Yasynuvata, Spartak, Novolaspa and Petrovske.<ref name=":9" /><ref name=":10" />

=== 28 April ===
The spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 53 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--3 WIA--><ref name=MoD6am04-28>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/28/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-27-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 27 квітня 2018 року |trans-title=Information by ATO HQ on 27 April 2018 |date=28 April 2018 |accessdate=28 April 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 50 occasions in Donetsk region and on 3 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=noon04-28ru/>); the fire was returned on more than 20 occasions.<ref name=noon04-28ru/> By 9:00&nbsp;am of 28 April 10 ceasefire violations were registered.<ref name=noon04-28ru/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded in action in the Donbass region on 27 April.<ref name=noon04-28ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/66489-prauta-18 |title=Боевики совершили 53 обстрела, применили минометы – полковник Праута |trans-title= |date=2018-04-28 |accessdate=2018-04-28 |publisher=MoD |language=ru |location=}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported 17 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in 12 different locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dan-news.info/defence/ukrainskie-siloviki-za-sutki-vypustili-po-dnr-svyshe-750-boepripasov-sckk.html|title=Украинские силовики за сутки выпустили по ДНР свыше 750 боеприпасов – СЦКК {{!}} ДАН|website=dan-news.info|language=ru-RU|access-date=2018-04-28}}</ref><ref name=":9">{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-stskk-2/|title=Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-27|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-29|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref name=":10">{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-trem-napravleniyam/|title=Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по трем направлениям {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-27|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-29|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/28/za-aprel-vosemnadtsat-mirnyh-grazhdan-poluchili-raneniya-i-pyatero-bylo-ubito-basurin/|title=За апрель восемнадцать мирных граждан получили ранения и пятеро было убито — Басурин|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-04-29|language=ru-RU}}</ref> In the territory of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic, local officials recorded seven Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire, The Ukrainian military engaged rebel positions at Pervomaisk, Sentianivka, Zholobok, Donetskyi, Kalynove and Kalinivka using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/28/lnr-operativnaya-svodka-obstrelyany-shest-poselkov/|title=ЛНР: оперативная сводка – обстреляны шесть поселков|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-04-29|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the information provided by the JFO press-centre in the evening, as of 6:00&nbsp;pm pro-Russian forces had opened fire on positions of Ukrainian troops on 21 occasions, three Ukrainian servicemen were wounded and two were injured.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1937280392949424 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 28 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-28 |accessdate=2018-04-28 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> In the environs of Donetsk city, Avdiivka became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns, grenade launchers, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars. Novotroitske was hit by 120&#160;mm mortar barrages, while 82&#160;mm mortar volleys landed in Novoselivka and Butivka mining complex. Rebel forces fired small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers at Marinka, Kamianka, Novotroitske, Opytne, Krasnohorivka, Verkhnyotoretske and Butivka miniing complex. Sniper fire was reported at Marinka. In the region of Mariupol, 120&#160;mm mortar rounds hit Bohdanivka, while Vodiane came under 82&#160;mm mortar fire. The separatists employed infantry weapons and rocket launchers to attack Ukrainian positions at Pavlopil, Hnutove, Vodiane, Shyrokyne and Lebedinske. Sniper fire was reported at Shyrokyne. In the northern section of the demarcation line, pro-Russian tanks engaged Ukrainian redoubts at Krymske, supported by 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery. Heavy shelling was likewise reported at Novotoshkivke, where Ukrainian forces were pounded by 120&#160;mm mortars, 122&#160;mm artillery and 152&#160;mm artillery. Luhanske and Troitske came under 120&#160;mm mortar fire. Prychepylivka and Novozvanivka were targeted by 82&#160;mm mortars. Antitank rockets landed in Popasna and Luhanske. Armoured fighting vehicles opened fire at Ukrainian forces around Troitske. Ukrainian troops at Novoselivka were harassed with small arms fire. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 61, one more Ukrainian soldier was wounded and one more injured.<ref name=MoD7am04-29/> Pro-Russian officials reported two civilian residents killed, one seriously injured, two houses and a bus destroyed in the course of heavy shelling on Dokuchaievsk, in the southern outskirts of Donetsk city. The town was shelled by tanks and 120&#160;mm mortars firing from Novotroitske.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dan-news.info/defence/podrazdeleniya-vsu-obstrelyali-dokuchaevsk-iz-minometov-i-tankovyx-orudij-sckk.html|title=Подразделения ВСУ обстреляли Докучаевск из минометов и танковых орудий – СЦКК {{!}} ДАН|website=dan-news.info|language=ru-RU|access-date=2018-04-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dan-news.info/defence/dva-cheloveka-pogibli-odin-ranen-v-dokuchaevske-xode-massirovannogo-obstrela-so-storony-vsu-sckk.html|title=Два человека погибли, один ранен в Докучаевске в ходе массированного обстрела со стороны ВСУ – СЦКК {{!}} ДАН|website=dan-news.info|language=ru-RU|access-date=2018-04-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dan-news.info/defence/obstrelami-so-storony-ukrainskoj-armii-v-dokuchaevske-povrezhdeno-dva-doma-basurin.html|title=Обстрелами со стороны украинской армии в Докучаевске повреждено два дома – Басурин {{!}} ДАН|website=dan-news.info|language=ru-RU|access-date=2018-04-29}}</ref> Ukrainian forces from Avdiivka fired small arms, heavy machine guns, rocket propelled grenades, 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortars at the water purification plant at Yasynuvata; the compound had to be shut down once again, despite the presence of OSCE mission monitors.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vnov-otkryli-ogon-po-yasinovatoj-vo-vremya-peresmenki-na-dfs/|title=ВСУ вновь открыли огонь по Ясиноватой во время пересменки на ДФС / AFU again opened fire on Yasinovataya during the shift turnover at the DFS {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-28|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-29|language=ru-RU}}</ref> Zaitseve, north of Horlivka, also came under mortar fire during the visit of German and Russian [[Non-governmental organization|NGO]]<nowiki/>s volunteers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dan-news.info/defence/delegaty-iz-germanii-i-rossii-stali-svidetelyami-obstrela-poselka-zajcevo-ukrainskimi-silovikami.html|title=Делегаты из Германии и России стали свидетелями обстрела поселка Зайцево украинскими силовиками {{!}} ДАН|website=dan-news.info|language=ru-RU|access-date=2018-04-29}}</ref> Ukrainian fire damaged a high power line at Krasny Partizan.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/pri-obstrele-v-sele-krasnyj-partizan-obestochena-podstantsiya-bez-elektrosnabzheniya-537-abonentov/|title=При обстреле в селе Красный Партизан обесточена подстанция, без электроснабжения 537 абонентов {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-28|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-29|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

=== 29 April ===
According to the information provided by the spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters in the morning, pro-Russian troops had opened fire on 61 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--4 WIA, 3 injured--><ref name=MoD7am04-29>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/29/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-28-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 28 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=2018-04-29 |access-date=2018-04-29 |publisher=Press-centre of the ATO HQ |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 51 occasions in Donetsk and on 10 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=MoD_noon04-29_ua/>); the fire was returned on 30 occasions.<ref name=MoD_noon04-29_ua/> From the midnight of 29 April till 9:00&nbsp;am 11 ceasefire violations were registered in Donetsk and 1 in Luhansk region; the fire was returned on 7 occasions.<ref name=MoD_noon04-29_ua/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that four Ukrainian servicemen were wounded and three were injured in the Donbass region on 28 April.<ref name=MoD_noon04-29_ua>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/29/brifing-rechnika-ministerstva-oboroni-ukraini-shhodo-situaczii-na-linii-zitknennya/ |title=Брифінг речника Міністерства оборони України щодо ситуації на лінії зіткнення |trans-title= |date=2018-04-29 |accessdate=2018-04-29 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city recorded 12 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in nine different areas using small arms, heavy machine guns, snipers, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-12-raz-narushili-peremirie-stskk/|title=ВСУ 12 раз нарушили перемирие — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-29|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-29|language=ru-RU}}</ref> In the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic, local officials reported seven Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire. The Ukrainian military used small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars and BMP-1 armoured vehicles to engage pro-Russian positions at Veselehorivka, Kalynove, Donetskyi, Nyzhnie Lozove and Zholobok.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://goves.net/news/1558-operativnaja-svodka-ot-narodnoi-milicii-za-proshedshie-sutki-29-aprelja-2018-goda.html|title=Оперативная сводка от Народной Милиции за прошедшие сутки 29 апреля 2018 года|website=Социальная сеть Новороссии|access-date=2018-04-29}}</ref>

The press-centre of the JFO reported in the evening that as of&nbsp;6:00 pm pro-Russian troops had opened fire on Ukrainian troops on 13 occasions, no casualties were reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts/1938377082839755 |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО станом на 18.00 29 квітня 2018 року |trans-title= |date=29 April 2018 |accessdate=29 April 2018 |publisher= |language=uk|website=www.facebook.com/ato.news/posts}}</ref> In the area of Donetsk city, the Ukrainian stronghold of Avdiivka became the target of small arms, heavy machine guns, rocket launchers and 82&#160;mm mortars. Rebel forces used infantry weapons and grenade launchers to target Ukrainian troops at Marinka, Krasnohorivka, Kamianka, Pisky, Opytne, Pisky and Nevelske. In the region of Mariupol, Pavlopil, Lebedinske and Shyrokyne were fired at from small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers. Antitank guided missiles were launched at Vodiane. In the northern sector of the demarcation line, Prychepylivka was pounded by 122&#160;mm self-propelled artillery, while Novozvanivka was hit by 82&#160;mm mortar volleys. The separatists attacked Novhorodske with rocket launchers, antiaircraft guns and 82&#160;mm mortars. Small arms fire was reported at Stanytsia Luhanska. By the end of the day the number of registered ceasefire violations had risen to 47, one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded and one was injured.<ref name=MoD6am04-30/> Pro-Russian authorities told the press that Ukrainian forces broke the ceasefire several times throughout the day. Dokuchaievsk, Spartak, Yakovliivka and Kruta Balka, in the outskirts of Donetsk city, Ozeryanivka and Zaitseve, in the area of Horlivka, and Petrovske in the region of Mariupol, came under attack. In the main incidents, Ukrainian tanks engaged pro-Russian positions at Dokuchaievsk, which also became the target of 120&#160;mm mortars. Ozeryanivka was attacked by BTR-80 armoured personnel carriers and BMP-2 armoured vehicles from Troitske, while Yakovliivka was shelled with automatic grenade launchers. BMP-2 armoured vehicles also opened fire at Petrovske and Spartak. Heavy fire destroyed two civilian residences at Zaitseve.<ref>• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-dokuchaevsk-i-petrovskoe-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Докучаевск и Петровское — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-po-n-p-ozeryanovka-stskk/ Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ по н.п. Озеряновка — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-obstrelyali-yakovlevku-stskk/ ВСУ обстреляли Яковлевку — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-otkryli-ogon-iz-tankov-po-dokuchaevsku-stskk/ ВСУ открыли огонь из танков по Докучаевску — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://dnr-online.ru/vsu-vedut-ogon-po-territorii-respubliki-stskk/ ВСУ ведут огонь по территории Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР].<br />• [https://news-front.info/2018/04/29/ukrainskie-siloviki-nanesli-udary-po-zajtsevo-unichtozheny-dva-domostroeniya-prihodko/ Украинские силовики нанесли удары по Зайцево, уничтожены два домостроения – Приходько], 2018-04-29</ref>

=== 30 April ===
The spokesman of the Ukrainian operational headquarters reported in the morning that pro-Russian forces had opened fire on 47 occasions on Ukrainian positions the previous day<!--1 WIA, 1 injured--><ref name=MoD6am04-30>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/30/zvedennya-pres-czentru-shtabu-ato-za-dobu-29-kvitnya-2018-roku/ |title=Зведення Прес-центру штабу АТО за добу 29 квітня 2018 року |trans-title=Information by ATO HQ on 29 April 2018 |date=30 April 2018 |accessdate=30 April 2018 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> (including on 42 occasions in Donetsk region and on 5 occasions in Luhansk region<ref name=MoD_1230-04-30_uk/>); the fire was returned on 19 occasions.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-30_uk/> By 9:00&nbsp;am of 30 April 9 ceasefire violations were registered.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-30_uk/> The spokesman of the Ministry of Defence confirmed at noon that one Ukrainian serviceman was wounded in action and another injured in the Donbass region on 29 April.<ref name=MoD_1230-04-30_uk>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/news/2018/04/30/brifing-rechnika-ministerstva-oboroni-ukraini-shhodo-situaczii-na-linii-zitknennya/ |title=Брифінг речника Міністерства оборони України щодо ситуації на лінії зіткнення |trans-title= |date=2018-04-30 |accessdate=2018-04-30 |publisher=MoD |language=uk}}</ref> Pro-Russian officials at Donetsk city reported 16 Ukrainian violations of the ceasefire in ten locations using small arms, heavy machine guns, automatic grenade launchers, 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles, 82&#160;mm mortars, 120&#160;mm mortars, armoured personnel carriers and armoured fighting vehicles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/za-sutki-vsu-narushili-rezhim-prekrashheniya-ognya-16-raz-stskk/|title=За сутки ВСУ нарушили режим прекращения огня 16 раз — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-30|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-04-30|language=ru-RU}}</ref> One civilian resident was wounded at Olenivka.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/v-rezultate-obstrela-so-storony-vsu-olenovki-ranen-mirnyj-zhitel-eduard-basurin/|title=В результате обстрела со стороны ВСУ Оленовки ранен мирный житель — Эдуард Басурин {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-30|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-05-01|language=ru-RU}}</ref> According to local sources, the Ukrainian military broke the ceasefire four times within the borders of the self-styled Luhansk People's Republic. Ukrainian forces engaged pro-Russian positions at Prishib, Lozove, Kalynove and Lohvynove employing small arms, 73&#160;mm rifles and 82&#160;mm mortars.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/30/lnr-operativnaya-svodka-obstrelyany-chetyre-poselka-3/|title=ЛНР: оперативная сводка — обстреляны четыре поселка|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-04-30|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

According to the Joint Forces Operation (JFO) headquarters, pro-Russian forces opened fire on Ukrainian positions on multiple occasions throughout the day. In the outskirts of Donetsk city, Novotroitske and Butivka coal mine were shelled with 120&#160;mm mortars; 82&#160;mm mortar volleys struck Verkhnyotoretske and Butivka. Pro-Russian armoured fighting vehicles, supported by small arms, heavy machine guns and rocket launchers engaged Ukrainian redoubts at Kamianka, Krasnohorivka, Avdiivka, Marinka, Verkhnyotoretske, Opytne and Butivka mining complex. In the region of Mariupol, Lebedinske and Talakivka came under 82&#160;mm mortars. Vodiane, Pyshchevik, Lebedinske, Hnutove Pavlopil, Shyrokyne and Taramchik were attacked with infantry weapons, grenade launchers and armoured fighting vehicles. in the northern sector of the demarcation line, armoured fighting vehicles opened fire on Ukrainian forces at Luhanske, Valuiske, Novhorodske and Troitske supported by infantry weapons and rocket launchers.<ref name=noon05-01ru>{{cite web|url=http://uacrisis.org/ru/66508-prauta-21 |title=Боевики 44 раза прицельно обстреляли украинские позиции – полковник Праута |trans-title= |date=2018-05-01 |accessdate=2018-05-01 |publisher=MoD |language=ru}}</ref> Pro-Russian authorities at Donetsk city reported a number of Ukrainian violations of the truce by evening. The Ukrainian military targeted Dokuchaievsk, Spartak, Vasiliivka, Volvo Center, Donetsk airport and Mykhailivka, in the surroundings of Donetsk city, Ozeryanivka, Zaitseve and Shyroka Balka, in the area of Horlivka, and in the region of Mariupol, Sakhanka, Uzhivka, Bezimenne and Pikuzy. In the main incidents, Dokuchaievsk and Bezimenne were hit by 82&#160;mm and 120&#160;mm mortar rounds, while 120&#160;mm mortar volleys landed in Shyroka Balka and Donetsk airport. Rebel forces also fired 82&#160;mm mortars at Spartak. BTR-80 armoured personnel carriers from Verkhnyotoretske attacked Mikhaylivka, and 73&#160;mm antitank recoilless rifles were fired several times at pro-Russian positions around Pikuzy. Small arms, heavy machine guns and automatic grenade launchers were widely used elsewhere.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovany-obstrely-so-storony-vsu-po-neskolkim-napravleniyam-respubliki-stskk/|title=Зафиксированы обстрелы со стороны ВСУ по нескольким направлениям Республики — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-30|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-05-01|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dnr-online.ru/zafiksirovan-obstrel-so-storony-vsu-donetska-i-dokuchaevska-stskk/|title=Зафиксирован обстрел со стороны ВСУ Донецка и Докучаевска — СЦКК {{!}} Официальный сайт ДНР|date=2018-04-30|work=Официальный сайт ДНР|access-date=2018-05-01|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news-front.info/2018/04/30/peremirie-prodolzhaetsya-vsu-vedut-obstrely-dnr/|title="Перемирие продолжается": ВСУ ведут обстрелы ДНР|work=News Front - Новостной Фронт. Новости Мира России Украины|access-date=2018-05-01|language=ru-RU}}</ref>

The [[President of Ukraine]] signed a decree on ending the [[Timeline of the war in Donbass (April–June 2014)#ATO|ATO]] that started in April 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mil.gov.ua/en/news/2018/04/30/president-signed-a-decree-the-joint-forces-operation-on-deflection-and-deterrence-of-russias-armed-aggression-in-the-donbas-began-on-april-30-2018/ |title=President signed a Decree: The Joint Forces Operation on deflection and deterrence of Russia's armed aggression in the Donbas began on April 30, 2018 |date=2018-04-30 |accessdate=2018-04-30 |publisher=[[Ministry of Defence (Ukraine)|MoD]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-27035196 |title=Ukraine says Donetsk 'anti-terror operation' under way |publisher=[[BBC News Online]] |date=16 April 2014 |accessdate=16 April 2014 }}</ref> The [[United States Department of State|US State Department]] meanwhile confirmed the delivery of [[FGM-148 Javelin]] antitank missiles to the Ukrainian army. The first batch of missiles had already been handed over in December 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.unian.info/politics/10100138-u-s-confirms-delivery-of-javelin-antitank-missiles-to-ukraine.html|title=U.S. confirms delivery of Javelin antitank missiles to Ukraine|access-date=2018-05-01|language=en}}</ref>

